title: italian potato salad
directions: Cut up potatoes in a large bowl. Add chopped onion, pepper and black olives. Add the oil, vinegar, black pepper and salt.
Mix together. Add eggs last, cut into wedges.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits and cut in half.
Place 1/4 apple in center of each biscuit.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll biscuits around apples and place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Heat margarine, water, white sugar and brown sugar to just melt.
Pour over dumplings and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oatmeal pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with soda.
Combine butter, sugar and pudding and beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs; gradually add to flour mixture, then stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lime jello salad(congealed)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Boil pineapple and sugar together until sugar dissolves.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Congeal.
Then add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add nuts, mix well.
Set in refrigerator until firm.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Roll chicken in mixture and bake 20 minutes on each side at 400°.
Blend soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in oil.
Remove from skillet.
Combine garlic, green pepper and soy sauce.
Add water to flour to make a paste. Stir into skillet mix.
Add steak and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with marshmallows. Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over marshmallows.
Crush strawberries and combine with dry gelatin mix.
Spoon strawberries and gelatin over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Strawberries sink to the bottom and marshmallows rise to the top to create a glaze.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Spray 9 x 10-inch pan with PAM.
Mix all ingredients, reserving about 1 c. of cheese for top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dressed bananas
directions: After bananas are peeled and sliced in halves, spread salad dressing on the banana halves, then roll each half into a spread of crushed peanuts.
Then with a sheet of wax paper laid in a large dessert plastic dish (Tupperware), lay them in it, shaking off extra peanuts.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in flour, mixing well.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this crumb mixture to sprinkle over cake before baking.
Add the egg, salt, buttermilk, baking soda, spices, raisins and nuts to the remaining crumb mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to sugar and margarine (dry ingredients then milk; flour first/flour last).
Add cocoa and hot water.
Stir, makes paste and then add to the mixture.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool and spread the filling between two cookies.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, add rest of the ingredients and mix lightly.
Fry, turning once.

title: southern honey bread
directions: In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
In small bowl, combine buttermilk, honey and egg.
Pour into dry ingredients and stir until mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serving Size:
1/2-inch slice.

title: fresh cucumber pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, salt and onion and let set 2 hours.
Drain. Mix sugar and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let set 1 1/2 hours. Do not cook.
Pack in freezer containers and freeze.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake about 45 minutes.

title: no cook whipped cream icing
directions: Cream the first three ingredients well with mixer. Alternately add the last three ingredients, beating well with each addition.
Frost the cake.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
In a saucepan, mix barbecue sauce and grape jam; let boil.
Add hot dogs.
Let all boil 15 minutes.
Pour into crock-pot.
Keep warm until ready to serve.

title: baked beans with ground beef
directions: Mix meat, onions, celery and pepper in skillet with cooking oil. Cook until nearly done. Drain oil out. Add brown sugar and catsup.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Pour beans into a casserole dish. Pour meat mixture over beans and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt butter. On wax paper, combine bread crumbs, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter, then roll in crumbs to coat.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Add wine, onion and parsley to remaining butter.
When chicken is golden brown, pour the butter sauce over it.
Return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add vinegar and beet liquid. Cook and stir constantly until thickened and clear.
Add beets and margarine.
Heat and serve.

title: four fruit punch
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients, stirring until sugar is completely dissolved.
Chill.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: kass's toffee squares(unbelievable!)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar; blend egg and salt, vanilla.
Add flour.
Spread into 10 x 15 1/2-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread with melted chocolate while hot. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook cabbage, potatoes and onion until tender.
Add corn, carrots, peas, green beans, whole tomatoes and tomato juice.
Salt and season to taste.
Bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water until thread spins. Add peanuts. Stir continuously after peanuts are added.
Cook until mixture turns a brownish gold. Take from heat. Stir in butter and salt. Add baking soda quickly. Stir until light and foamy.

title: glorious macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni and saute onions and pimento in margarine until crisp.
Mix with other ingredients.
Spoon into greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt evelyn's chicken supreme
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, pepper, salt and garlic.
Coat breasts well with sour cream mixture.
Place on a nonstick baking sheet that has been brushed with butter.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.
Before baking, roll chicken in bread crumbs. Drizzle with half of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Drizzle with remaining margarine and return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole(serves 4)
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add 2 tablespoons butter, onions, salt, pepper and squash.
Boil until squash is tender.
Drain squash and mash.
In a saucepan, on low, add 1/2 stick butter and brown sugar.
Crumble crackers and add to pan.
Scramble eggs and add to pan.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Crumble potato chips on top of dish until chips cover top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until set.

title: carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients and carrots.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add nuts and blend well.
Turn into an oiled 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool, remove from pans and turn onto wire racks.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of a double boiler. Stir in 8 egg yolks and milk; blend well.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Remove
from heat. Add vanilla.
Layer bottom of a casserole dish with vanilla wafers.
Top with a layer of sliced bananas.
Pour about 1/3 of custard over bananas.
Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard to make 3 layers of each, ending with the custard.

title: pineapple delight(makes 2)
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs.
Mix sugar, butter and eggs well. Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Beat until it is fluffed up.
Take bowl and put layer of wafers, then filling.
Repeat as desired. End with layer of filling.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt in bowl.
Melt oleo and shortening in a pan.
Add cocoa and hot water; let come to a boil. Pour over flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and buttermilk/soda mixture.
Beat with cake batter and add vanilla. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in 11 x 16-inch pan.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat 2 inches of oil in heavy skillet (350°).
Pour 1/2 cup of batter in funnel into hot oil.
Turn when golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
Beat egg with wire whisk and mix in water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture and combine thoroughly.
Makes at least 5 pie crusts.
May be put into pie plate (ready to bake).
Cover well and freeze until needed.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Whip the first 3 ingredients.
Add drained pineapple and whole cranberry sauce; add nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Cut in squares.
Serve with a "dab" of dressing on top.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour or cornstarch and salt. Gradually add milk, mixing well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount hot mixture into egg yolks; immediately return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut. Pour into cooled baked 9-inch pastry shell.
Spread one recipe Meringue atop hot pie; sprinkle with 1/3 cup coconut.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden.
Cool.

title: potato wedges
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese, flour, chicken seasoning and pepper together.
Coat potatoes with dry mixture; place in shallow pan. Pour the margarine over the potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Place half the noodles in the bottom of a baking dish, the the bean sprouts, next the celery and onion mixture, then the chicken, mushroom soup and then the rest of the noodles.
Top with the nuts.

title: pumpkin bread with cranberries
directions: Put all ingredients into a large bowl and beat for 3-5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: our favorite venison dinner
directions: Slice venison in very thin slices (it cuts best when still a bit frozen).
Quick fry in a small amount of oil, seasoning liberally and browning on both sides.
Place in an oven roaster or casserole dish.
Saute onions and garlic.
Add to venison.
Add soup, mushrooms and 3/4 cup water.
Stir together.
Cover and simmer in oven at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: golden potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix corn flake crumbs and salt. Brush potatoes with butter; coat with crumbs. Arrange in ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches. Bake, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cool.
Remove bones and skin. Melt margarine or butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix stuffing mix in the melted margarine or butter.
In Dutch oven or large pan, mix the soup and chicken broth.
Add stuffing mix and chicken.
Save about 1 1/2 cups of stuffing to put on top of casserole.
Pour mixture back into baking dish butter was melted in.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 425° or until brown on top.
Recipe may be divided.

title: delicious fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a plastic bag; shake to mix and set aside.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Place 2 or 3 pieces of chicken in bag; shake well.
Repeat procedure with remaining chicken.
Heat 1-inch of oil in a large skillet to 325°; add chicken and fry 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain chicken on paper towels.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together until creamy and fluffy.
Add egg and then add dry ingredients, sifted together, alternately with sour cream.
Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out and put on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes in center of a 400° oven until lightly brown.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: garlic almonds
directions: If the almonds have shells on them, soak them in very hot water for a few minutes.
Drain them and then slide the skins off. Put them on a paper towel covered cookie sheet and let them dry out well (put them in a low oven for a faster job).
Fill a fry pan with about 1 1/2 inches of oil.
Heat the oil and then put the almonds in the oil.

Turn frequently until they are golden brown. With a slotted spoon, put them on a paper towel to drain off. Empty them into a bowl and sprinkle garlic salt over them, turning them all until well covered.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and add water to make 3 cups.
Cook pudding mixes in the juice.
Cool; add the fruit.
You may also add bananas and maraschino cherries if desired.
Chill.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: A little finely chopped onion and celery.
Stir together. Chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Layer in large Pyrex dish (or 2 small dishes), rice, chicken and soups.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Layer cheese and almonds on top and bake for an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini, flour, soda, salt and baking soda.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown the first 2 ingredients and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until hot; serve on a bun.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine Jello and boiling water; add sugar and cornstarch and boil 1 minute.
Let cool.
Slice strawberries into a baked pie crust.
Cover with cooled syrup.
Chill and serve with Cool Whip. Serves 6.

title: blueberry bars
directions: Heat oven to 305°.
Mix 1 cup flour, butter and sugar until smooth.
Spread evenly in the bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir remaining ingredients (except pecans) into slightly beaten eggs.
Spread over top of baked cookie base and top with chopped nuts.
Bake 25 minutes more.
Cool; cut in 3 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 20 bars.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Mix together.
Bring to hard-boil stage.
When mixture turns golden brown, pour into buttered pan.
When candy is just warm, sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
When they melt, spread on top. Let cool overnight, then crack with a knife.

title: sweet dough for dinner rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a large bowl. Stir well to blend.
Add soft margarine to hot tap water and add to ingredients in bowl.
Beat 2 minutes with electric beater. Add beaten eggs and 1 more cup of flour.
Beat at high speed 1 minute.
Gradually add remaining flour (enough for a stiff, kneadable dough) and knead for 10 minutes until smooth.
Cover for 20 minutes to let rise in warm place.
After 20 minutes, punch down, divide, and shape into dinner rolls.
Let rise and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(This dough can also be made into bread and cinnamon rolls.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with 1 1/2 cups water.
Mix and add dry pudding.
Blend well and add 1 1/2 containers Cool Whip.
Layer bananas, crackers and pudding mixture.
Top with leftover Cool Whip and sprinkle graham crackers over top.

title: hot coco mix
directions: Use 2 heaping tbsp to one cup hot water.

title: chicken broccoli stir-fry
directions: Mix soy sauce, cornstarch, chicken broth and ginger. Set aside.
Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons oil in wok or large skillet. Stir-fry chicken and red pepper over medium-high heat until pink is gone (about 3 minutes).
Remove from wok.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to wok. Stir-fry onion, garlic, red and green bell peppers 2 to 3 minutes (until onion is tender).
Add broccoli and remaining oil to wok.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add chicken and broth mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened (2 to 3 minutes). Serve with rice. Serves 4.

title: salmon mousse with sour cream dill sauce
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water, add boiling water and stir until gelatin has dissolved.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, Tabasco, paprika and salt and mix well.
Chill to consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Add salmon and capers and beat well.
Whip the cream, fold into salmon mixture and turn into a 2-quart oiled fish mold.
Add the cheese to fill the mold.
Chill until set. Unmold onto a serving platter and garnish with watercress, lemon slices, parsley and/or olives.
Serve with Dill Sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dr. dalton's original fried turkey
directions: Mix all ingredients, except turkey.
Inject mixture into turkey.
Put turkey in plastic bag and refrigerate overnight.
Fry turkey for 4 minutes per pound at 300°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and celery in butter or oil. Add other ingredients and simmer until thick.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Cook
crushed pineapple and juice.
Add vanilla pudding mix. Bring
to
a boil.	Cool completely in the refrigerator. Stir in about
1/3 of Cool Whip until completely mixed.
Fold in remaining Cool Whip.	Frost round layer cake (4 layers).

title: dump cake
directions: Layer each ingredient as listed.
Do not mix together.
Bake 1 hour in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°.
(Blueberry is also very good.)

title: cinda's spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Set aside.
Cook bacon to crisp. (I cook bacon in microwave, reserving 8 pieces).
Reserve bacon fat.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix together; add to casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with rolls and fruit salad.
Very tasty for a quick meal.

title: french cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin pans.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon in mixing bowl; set aside.
In another bowl beat eggs; stir in butter and milk.
Add liquid ingredients all at once to flour mixture.
Stir only until flour is moistened.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake about 15 minutes or until done.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Divide into 2 equal sections.
Add colors into dough.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Put darker layer on bottom.
Moisten, then put lighter on top and press together.
Then roll, chill for 3 hours and cut 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Grease a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet; line with wax paper.
Mix ingredients together well; pour onto wax papered pan.
Sprinkle the pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When done, flip out onto cup towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar. Roll while hot.
Let cool for about 2 hours.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Place the whole chicken in a deep baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour half over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Baste every 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill at least 20 minutes.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press crescent rolls to cover bottom of 15 x 11 x 1-inch pan. Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, mayo and dressing mix until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle vegetables on filling.
Press vegetables into filling slightly.
Refrigerate and cut into bars.

title: seven-up salad(lemon)
directions: Mix lemon jello, hot water and 7-Up and chill until jelly consistency.
Add miniature marshmallows, pineapple and bananas. Stir until mixed and chill.

title: bridget's oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Beat sugars and butter until creamy, add eggs and vanilla, beat well.
In small bowl, mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt, add to sugar/egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins, mix well.
Drop tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10-12 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet and then transfer to wire rack.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes in boiling salted water.
Do not drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix onion, broccoli and soup.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir until cheese is melted.
Stir in rice and pour into a casserole dish; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If too soupy, add an additional 1/2 cup rice before baking.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: grilled cheese sandwiches
directions: Put butter on 2 pieces of bread.
Put cheese on both of them. Put them on the stove at 300°.
Wait about 15 minutes, then eat it.

title: goldenrod eggs
directions: Mix butter and flour.
Add milk and cook to make a white sauce or gravy.
Add chopped whites of eggs to white sauce.
Serve over toast and sprinkle with egg yolks which have been put through a sieve or chopped real fine.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreo cookies (reserve about half the amount).
Use other crumbs, mixed with melted margarine to make crust.
Mix milk, cream cheese and pudding mix together.
Fold in Coool Whip.
Put mixture on top of crust, then sprinkle remaining amount of crumbs on the top of this.
Freeze or refrigerate for several minutes, if you wish.

title: amaretto cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix the cream cheese, Ricotta and sour cream with an electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 2 minutes each time.
Add cooled melted butter, sugar, flour and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add Amaretto, almond extract and vanilla.
Pour into a 10-inch greased spring-form pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and leave cheesecake in oven with door closed for 1 more hour.
Remove from oven, cool and refrigerate.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: super crisp fried chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium high heat.
Batter chicken by dipping in a mixture of egg and milk followed by the flour mixed with all the spices.
Brown chicken on all sides. Reduce heat to medium and continue to cook until chicken is tender (around 40 minutes).
Do not cover.
Turn chicken during cooking.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° until done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add broccoli, onion, corn muffin mix, salt, cottage cheese and melted oleo.
Pour into hot skillet and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy amy's way
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4 pieces.
Drop into hot grease and fry until biscuits float.
Drain on a napkin.
Sprinkle sugar on top. Easy made donuts!

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Bring butter and water to a boil.
Stir in sugar and dry milk; beat well.
Best used when first made.
Use in recipes calling for condensed milk.

title: claudia's pasta
directions: Cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Add spices and cook over low heat at least 30 minutes.
Cook pasta according to box directions. Drain.
Add cheese and milk to tomato mixture; warm slowly.
Pour sauce over pasta.
Serve in bowls with lots of garlic French bread.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat all the ingredients until smooth and well blended.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan (11 x 15 approximately).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk together in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheesy pretzels
directions: Mix flour, cheeses, Italian seasoning, garlic and onion powder together.
Cut in 1/4 cup butter (until it resembles a coarse corn meal texture).
Add milk gradually until mixture sticks.
Chill. Divide into 12 even pieces.
Roll 8 to 10-inches long and divide into thirds.
Shape into pretzels.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lightning cake
directions: Mix together in a bowl the sugar, flour and baking powder. Fill a cup 1/4 full of melted butter. Break the eggs into this and fill cup with sweet milk. Add to dry mixture. Add vanilla and beat thoroughly. Bake 20 minutes.

title: real red devil's food cake
directions: Sift into bowl flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add shortening and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts. Beat 2 minutes longer.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: imperial fruit
directions: In bowl, combine pineapple, grapes and marshmallows.
In saucepot, blend 1/2 cup syrup from pineapple and 1/4 cup water with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until clear and thickened.
Stir in beaten egg a spoonful at a time.
Add dash of salt and heat.
Cool cooked mixture.
After thoroughly cooled, pour mixture over fruit and toss lightly.
Chill overnight. Before serving, fold in bananas (sliced), cherries and 1 cup heavy cream (whipped).

title: spanish squash(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute onions.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and simmer.
Add tomato sauce and thinly sliced squash.
Mix and season.
Cook until tender.
Add grated cheese and let melt.
Serve hot.

title: nutty tuna casserole
directions: In glass casserole, blend soup, water, tuna, celery, onion and cashews.
Sprinkle noodles over top. Cook 10 to 12 minutes, rotating dish halfway through cooking time.
Rest 5 minutes before serving.

title: blackened chicken salad
directions: Melt the butter.
Dip chicken in butter and dredge into mixture of all the spices.
Heat a heavy skillet to high heat. Drizzle a teaspoon of the butter onto the seasoned chicken and saute several at a time, butter side down, until blackened.
Turn and repeat.
Arrange the sliced chicken on a bed of mixed greens and serve with Honey-Mustard Dressing.

title: quick and easy pot roast
directions: Place roast in deep dish roasting pan.
Sprinkle soy sauce on roast.
Fill roasting pan with 2 to 3-inches of water, adding onions to water and bake at 200° to 250° all night long.
Don't worry about it!
In a.m., add carrots, potatoes, mushroom soup and soy sauce to taste.
Place back in oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
This will make a deliciously brown gravy on its own.
Serve with biscuits or rolls.
May also be served over fluffy rice.
Toss a quick green salad and they'll think you've been slaving over a stove all day.
Enjoy!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until honey colored.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour on greased (margarine) cookie sheet or marble.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Spoon into well greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 or 45 minutes.

title: mud hens
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add 2 egg yolks and 1 whole egg. Mix well.
Add flour and vanilla; mix well.
Spread in slightly greased 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff; add brown sugar and nuts.
Spread over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: old-fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with the sauce and syrup mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
This makes a large cake.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until tests done at 325° to 350°.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Roll out crescents. Spread 1 cup of grated cheese and chopped chicken onto rolls. Re-shape into crescents. Place in 9 x 13 baking dish. In small boiler, mix soups, 1 cup grated cheese and 1 cup milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Spread over roll-ups. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, until browned.

title: apple cake pie
directions: Place apples in well-greased 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cover with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix with creamed mixture.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef louise
directions: Mix all ingredients together in covered casserole.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Do not peek.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: super slush
directions: The day before serving, combine lemonade concentrate, orange juice concentrate, lemon-lime soda, pineapple, mixed fruits, oranges and bananas in a large mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Put into a container and freeze.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water.
When nearly done, add rest of ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: basic cheddar cheese sauce
directions: Combine soup with milk; heat.
Stir often.

title: turkey salad bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, put in refrigerator with 1/2 cup canning salt sprinkled on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Beat shortening until smooth. Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well. Sift all dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Might need more flour
until soft enough to roll out. Roll dough on a floured surface. Cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix as recipe.
Pour over coconut and nuts in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (Pam pan well first).
Melt stick of oleo.
Add cream cheese and sugar.
Drop by tablespoons over uncooked cake mix. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Will be gooey or bake for 1 hour for drier cake.

title: mary kilgore's ginger cakes
directions: Mix in order written here.
Use enough flour so it will make dough that you can roll out.
Pinch off piece of dough and roll out in 6-inch ovals and bake.

title: apricot balls
directions: Mix apricots, coconut, milk and nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Let stand 2 hours before packaging. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields 4 dozen candies.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and milk; add pumpkin.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Add salt and pumpkin mixture.
Beat well with electric mixer.
Pour into shell; dot with butter and sprinkle top lightly with nutmeg. Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.
A stainless knife blade carefully inserted in the center of the pie will come out clean if the pie is done.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: old-fashioned biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening until mealy.
Add milk; knead on floured board or wax paper as directed.
Roll to desired thickness and cut.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: festive shrimp dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in a 13 x 9-inch pan or platter. Pour cocktail sauce over top and spread evenly.
Crumble shrimp over top.
Chill and serve with crackers.
Amount of ingredients depends on size of dishes that are used.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all together.
Press through cookie press.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour once before measuring. Grease a loaf pan, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch size.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, slice bananas and beat until mashed.
Measure out 1 cup.
Sift together in a large bowl the flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Add shortening or butter, eggs, nuts and mashed bananas. Beat together until well blended.
Pour into prepared loaf pan and bake about 1 hour or until done.

title: reuben burger pie
directions: Combine meat shell ingredients and press into the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Drain.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix together and pour on top of chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wine rock cookies
directions: Prepare flour and baking soda and set aside.
Beat eggs with sugar and margarine.
Add sherry and spices.
Add flour with baking soda; mix well.
Gradually mix in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat with garlic and onion.
Add other ingredients; cook until done, on low heat for approximately 2 hours.

title: lemon pie
directions: In a large bowl, put the water, bread crumbs and butter; let set until soft, then beat with mixer until smooth. Add this to the other ingredients in a large saucepan and cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Pour into the baked pie shell and top with meringue or whipped topping.

title: "better than butter" butter
directions: Just mix the above ingredients together and chill.

title: apple pie(no apples)
directions: Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar.
Bring to a boil. Add Ritz crackers.
Do not stir.
Cook 2 minutes.
Pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle cinnamon and dot with butter. Put on slotted pie top crust.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: maple nut coffee twist
directions: 1st step: Dissolve yeast from the hot roll mix in warm water in a bowl. Stir in egg, sugar and flavoring. Knead on floured surface 2-3 minutes. Place in a greased bowl. Cover and let rise in warm place until double, 30 minutes-1 hour. Divide dough into 3 balls and roll each on a floured surface to fit a 12-inch round greased pan. Brush each section with melted butter.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Cook chopped celery and onions with broth until tender. Crumble cornbread, celery, onions and chopped chicken into mixer bowl.
Add all ingredients except butter.
Pour mixture into lightly greased crock pot.
Put the butter on top.
Cook on high 2 hours or on low 3-4 hours.

title: pichelsteiner topf (german)(mixed meat and vegetable stew)
directions: Cook bacon in a large Dutch oven until crisp.
Drain off fat. Place alternate layers of carrots, onion, meat and potatoes in Dutch oven. Add bouillon, salt, pepper and marjoram. Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for about 1 1/2 hours. Garnish with parsley before serving.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, melted butter, cinnamon and brown sugar like pie crust.
Pat half of mixture in a greased 9-inch pan. Cover with diced rhubarb.
Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until clear.
Add vanilla and pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Pour off excess fat.
Mix cheese, soup, milk, catsup and olives together in a bowl.
Mix beef and soup mixture and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°, then top casserole with biscuits and bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: old-fashioned coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Mix Velveeta cheese and butter.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla
and nuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered pan (cookie sheet) and refrigerate for an hour.
Cut in squares.
Keep refrigerated and can be frozen.

title: delicious peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Cook until boiling. Boil for 10 full minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Mix well.
Then add marshmallow cream and mix well. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: mulled cider
directions: Simmer the cider and the cinnamon stick over medium heat until the bubbles appear around the edge and the surface begins to foam. Reduce the heat, sprinkle on the nutmeg and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together package of taco seasoning and cream cheese. Blend in sour cream.
Spread on bottom of 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with salsa to taste; top with lettuce and shredded cheese.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and meat; drain.
Add flour, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, mushrooms and water.
Stir and brown.
Add soup.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve noodles cooked as directed with stroganoff over them.

title: creamed leeks
directions: Trim and slice leeks crosswise, then wash them well.
In a heavy skillet, saute leeks in 1/4 cup olive oil for about 5 minutes.
Turn down heat. Cover tightly to steam for 10 minutes or so.
Put 1/4 cup olive oil in saucepan. Dissolve potato flour or brown rice flour in oil and heat until mixture bubbles. Stir in water. Continue to cook a minute or so until well combined.
Cook 10 minutes longer after adding leeks. Salt and pepper to taste. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp crab dip
directions: Melt butter; make sauce by adding whipping cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Add mushroom soup and sherry. Mix well. Add shrimp and crab meat. Serve in timbles. Serves 75.

title: mother's cheese delight
directions: Make in small balls.
Mash with a fork dipped in flour.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Cook in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: concord grape salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
When partially set, mix drained pineapple and pie filling.
When set, spread with other ingredients that have been mixed together.

title: potato salad for fifty
directions: Wash potatoes and cook in jackets until tender. Peel and cut in 1/2-inch cubes.
Pour French dressing over warm potatoes and let stand several hours.
Combine celery, salad dressing, parsley, onion and diced eggs. Salt and pepper to taste. Combine with potatoes and mix lightly.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute
onions
and
celery in large skillet.
Add mushrooms. Add
soup and
water.
Add	Cheez
Whiz.
Stir
until cheese melts.
Take from
burner and add rice (uncooked). Cook broccoli. Put in casserole
dish and add cheese mixture.
Mix well. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill and serve.
You may cut recipe in half.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix flour, crumbs, oleo and nuts together; spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together; pour into prepared crust. Spread pie filling on top and chill.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening to size of peas.
Sprinkle in water 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing with a fork until all flour is moistened (3 to 4 tablespoons more water may be added if needed).
Firmly press dough into a ball.
Divide in half.
Roll each half out to fit your pie pan, about 1/8-inch thick.
Makes 1 (2-crust) pie or two single crusts.

title: brie with sun-dried tomato topping
directions: Chill Brie well before handling.
Remove rind from top and place cheese on serving plate.
Combine ingredients; spread onto cheese.
Serve at once or refrigerate for later use.
For better flavor, allow Brie to stand 30 to 60 minutes when removed from refrigerator.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients except cucumbers in a microwave safe bowl. Mix well.
Add cucumbers and stir.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes; stirring every 2 minutes until cucumbers are crisp and tender and onion is translucent.
Ladle into jars.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Add jello to boiling water
and
stir to dissolve.
Add and mix remaining ingredients.	Pour in mold and chill.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Brown chicken and season to taste.
Place to side.
In a large mixing bowl, mix warmed broccoli, onions and cheese, then add chicken.
Place one egg roll wrap in a pot pie dish.
Fill with 1 mixing spoon size of mixture.
Fold closed and lightly spray with Pam.
Repeat until mixture is gone.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, until browned and warm throughout.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Mix syrup, butter and brown sugar in large bowl.
Add vanilla extract and oatmeal.
Mix together using fingers (mixture will be firm).
Mix in chocolate chips.

title: homemade cocoa mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a deep bowl and add as many marshmallows desired.
To make a cup of cocoa, simply add 1/3 cup mix to a cup of boiling water.
May use more mix, if necessary.

title: mom's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add milk in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: salad dressing spice or chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in small square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hawaiian sauce
directions: Puree all ingredients in food processor.
Marinate 6 skinless chicken breasts for 4 to 6 hours, then barbecue.

title: sausage-macaroni casserole
directions: Combine macaroni and cheese spread (may need to heat spread). Add milk, onion powder, mustard and sausage.
Place in a 4-quart casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons margarine with sugar.
Add egg and beat until creamy.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; spread batter in greased 8-inch square pan.

title: homemade butter pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix softened butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate flour, milk and vanilla until all ingredients are mixed smooth.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Bake 30 more minutes.
Should be golden brown and will be firm.

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with chunks of pineapple, cantaloupe, strawberries and grapes.

title: catfish pilaf
directions: Place catfish fillets in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with oleo and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Drain and flake.
Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp. Remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook green pepper and onion in drippings, stirring often, until tender. Stir in bacon, tomatoes and other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes (until liquid is absorbed).
Stir in catfish. Cover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in plastic bag, set aside.
Place Crisco and butter in a shallow pan (1-inch high).
Place in 400° oven and melt butter.
Wash chicken and remove all fat.
Shake wet chicken in plastic bag.
Place chicken skin side down in melted butter and turn right over.
Cook 20 minutes, turn and cook 20 minutes more and turn again.
Should be done in 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread #1
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Make a well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth by hand, pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni and tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni until desired firmness; drain.
In large bowl, combine macaroni, mayonnaise and tuna.
Stir until mixed well. Add olives and raisins.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; stir until mixed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take meat off bones.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in bottom of 7 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the stuffing mix over the margarine.
Spread the chicken over this.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover 15 minutes or until tender; drain and mash. Combine potatoes, cream cheese and next 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed (or by hand) until smooth. Spoon mixture into a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika. Cover and chill up to 24 hours. Remove from refrigerator; let stand, covered, 30 minutes. Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pie pan.
Bake at 325° first 30 minutes, then raise to 375°.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, then broth and milk.
Stir constantly until sauce begins to thicken and is smooth.
Add drained onions, almonds and seasonings.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs and cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: casserole hash
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan.
Put the meat first, then the onion, then the hash browns.
Pour soup on top of hash browns.
Spread evenly and bake at 350° for 2 hours. Can also add peas or corn if desired.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain vegetables and put in bowl. Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in pot and boil 5 to 6 minutes.
Pour hot vinegar solution over beans and stir well. Let stand overnight, then drain vinegar off.

title: jello delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 8 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
After it sets, cover with whipping cream or Cool Whip.
Serve. Delicious.

title: bean stew
directions: Fry onions and pepper.
Add spices, tomato sauce and chopped tomatoes.
Add beans.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Serve over brown rice.

title: beef dish
directions: Season, brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Mix rice, beef consomme, mushrooms and curry powder in with hamburger mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir it all together.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with sour cream; place a dab on top and mix in.
Great for parties; can be made ahead and frozen.

title: calico scallops saute
directions: In large nonstick skillet, melt margarine and add garlic. Cook until garlic is golden brown.
Add scallops and parsley and cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring often.
Sprinkle with pepper and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: meltaway cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir in flour and salt.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 1 inch apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set but not brown about 8 to 9 minutes.
While warm, roll into powdered sugar; cool.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: bol-go-ki
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except the meat together in one container.
Place the sliced meat in the container large enough to hold the 3 pounds with additional room to rotate the meat. As the meat is placed in the container, pour the ingredients over the layers of beef.
Allow to marinate 8 to 12 hours with rotation of the meat every 2 hours or so as in order to allow the seasoning to penetrate throughout.

title: caramel nut squares
directions: Cut shortening into flour as in making pastry; add egg and mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes.

title: sweet dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with any fresh fruits or vegetables.

title: crumb cake
directions: Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumb mixture for top.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour batter into greased and floured pans and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine fruit, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Blend into sour cream.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Toss with chicken and celery.
Cover and refrigerate.
Stir in grapes; serve in lettuce cups, if desired.

title: dressing for spinach salad
directions: Blend ingredients in blender or food processor.
Chill.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa. Add milk and melted butter in large saucepan. Bring to a boil and let boil 30 seconds, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and stir in. Add oatmeal. Stir and drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls. Let cool. Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: stew
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until tender.
Remove chicken from pot, set aside.
Cook potatoes and onion in broth until tender. Add tomatoes and corn.
Bring to boil.
Add chili powder and butter.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, red pepper and paprika. De-bone chicken and cut into bite sized pieces.
Add to mixture. Simmer 10 minutes and serve with corn bread.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and water. Beat for 10 minutes.
Mix topping ingredients together (sugar, cocoa, cinnamon and nuts).
Grease angel food pan and sprinkle a little topping around.
Add the cake batter and topping like for a marble cake. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix. Pour in greased dish. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until brown.

title: easy cocoa
directions: Use 2 tablespoons of
mix to 6 ounces of hot water or can add mix to taste.

title: mint julep fruit cup
directions: Combine fruit and spoon into compotes.
Sprinkle with creme de menthe or mint extract.
Serve with 1/4 cup of lime sherbet and garnish with a fresh mint leaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: soda cracker fudge
directions: Boil Pet milk and sugar for one full minute.
Add crackers, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Break bread into bite-sized pieces.
Spread evenly over bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over bread.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup, chicken noodle soup, egg and chicken.
Spread mixture over the bread in dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carbonnara
directions: Prepare pasta and keep in strainer.
In large saucepan, fry bacon; drain on paper towels.
In small saucepan, slowly warm whipping cream, red pepper and 1 tablespoon bacon drippings.
Beat eggs and add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
In large bowl, toss pasta, egg mixture, softened butter and cream mixture.
Keep on very low heat.
Crumble bacon and toss in.
Add remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Serve immediately.

title: lemon pepper orange roughy
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray shallow baking pan with nonstick coating.
Place fillets in pan.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper; drizzle with margarine.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or just until fish flakes easily.
Top with parsley.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Scald milk with rice.
Add sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Pour into casserole and bake at 325 for 1 hour 25 minutes or until almost set.
Stir every 20 minutes.
Ten to fifteen minutes before pudding is done, add 1/2 cup raisins and mix well.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Let cool in a bowl.
Put sauce in skillet; bring to a medium boil.
Arrange pepper halves on sauce, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: old fashioned corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Add egg, milk and oil. Stir to make a fairly smooth batter. Pour into greased pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pan or on wire rack. Cut into squares.
Serve warm or cold.

title: jello and sour cream ribbon jello
directions: Always mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot and 1/2 cup cold water. Grease pan with butter (13 x 9-inch).
Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour in pan and refrigerate until firm, approximately 40 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and shortening together.
Add egg, water and vinegar.
Mix until it forms a ball.
Roll out and fit in pie tin.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine butter, onion, bread crumbs, walnuts and parsley and stuff.
Bake at 300° for 10 - 20 minutes.

title: red  velvet cake
directions: Follow directions on box of cake mix and add food coloring.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces.
Brown meat in pan on stove.
Put meat in electric skillet.
Salt and pepper both sides of meat.
Cut up onion and add to meat.
Pour chili sauce over meat.
Add 2 cups water and stir.
Simmer for 2 hours, until meat is tender.
Keep skillet covered and turn meat gradually.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and curry powder.
Mix well. Drain fruit and arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Cover with mixture of butter, brown sugar and curry.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: carrot ring
directions: Combine first nine ingredients; mix well.
Beat the eggs puffy, fold into carrot mixture.
Pour into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn out onto a warm platter.
Fill center with warmed sweet English peas. Garnish outside ring with parsley.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: brandied peaches
directions: Rub fuzz from peaches with a coarse towel.
Mix sugar and water in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Add peaches and simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain peaches.
Place in sterilized quart jars (saving sugar).
Pour 1/4 cup brandy into each quart.
Pour syrup over peaches and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 15 minutes.
Store for 3 months in cool, dark place before using.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar, pumpkin, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Spread batter on waxed paper-lined pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Lay clean towel on table.
Flip cake onto towel.
Peel off paper and roll cake up while hot.
Let cool.
Unroll cake and spread the following filling.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix 6 tablespoons juice with flour, sugar and Cheddar cheese. Top with Ritz crackers mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place peeled and diced apples into a well-oiled casserole. Add water and sprinkle cinnamon.
Work together sugar, flour and butter until crumbly and spread on apples.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: danielle's favorite cornbread
directions: Beat 2 eggs slightly.
Add can of creamed corn, can of whole corn kernels, sour cream, melted butter, salt and pepper to taste. Mix well.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crackling bread
directions: If cracklings are large, put in blender or food processor until they are chopped in small pieces.
Mix cracklings with corn meal, flour and salt.
Add water until mixture is of desired consistency. Pour in baking dish.
Bake until brown.

title: chipped apple cake
directions: Dump all together in bowl and mix. Pour into funnel cake pan or large rectangular pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: low calorie orange chiffon cheesecake(by aunt kitty)
directions: Grease 9-inch spring-form pan lightly.
Blend cracker crumbs with margarine thoroughly and press over bottom and half up sides of pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: courtney's cookless play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and Kool-Aid.
Add oil and water.
Mix well with spoon.
When cool enough, mix with hands.
Store in Ziploc bags.

title: waldorf crown salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts. Pour into 5-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold; surround with lettuce.
Combine sour cream and Miracle Whip salad dressing. Fold miniature marshmallows into sour cream.
Fill center of mold with mixture.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices; mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.

title: watermelon bombe
directions: Chill batter bowl in freezer for 30 minutes. Remove and press lime sherbet into batter bowl, covering the sides and bottom. Return to freezer until firm. Repeat for lemon or pineapple sherbet and fill cavity with raspberry sherbet, mixed with chocolate chips. Freeze until very firm. Invert batter bowl on top of serving plate and wrap a warm, wet towel around bowl to loosen sherbet. Slice in "watermelon" wedges to serve. Yield: 14 to 16 servings.

title: working girl's rolls
directions: Mix flour and milk and add mayonnaise.
Mixture will be thin. Pour into muffin tins which have been well-greased.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until well browned.
If any is left over, wrap in foil and freeze.

title: broccoli cole slaw
directions: Mix all vegetables and sunflower seeds together in a large bowl. Then mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar in small bowl and pour over vegetables and blend well.

title: shells ala genovese
directions: Cook shells as directed on package.
Meanwhile, mix cream (or milk), Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, marjoram and nutmeg together in a bowl.
In a skillet, heat the margarine and cook the ham and peas until ham is lightly browned.
While pasta is draining, heat the cheese mixture in the pasta pan.
Lightly mix the drained pasta into the sauce.
Stir in the ham and peas mixture.
Serves 8.

title: easy onion rings
directions: Combine flour, beer, egg and salt.
Slice onion and separate into rings or quarter and separate layers.
Pieces will be in boat-like shapes.
Dip onions in batter.
Heat oil to 375°; add the batter-covered onions and fry until golden brown.

title: chili mac
directions: "Put the fish in microwave.
Take it out and put it in the oven for 5 minutes.
Take out and eat."

title: quicky sticky buns
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam spray.
Put doughballs in pan. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over doughballs.
Shake pudding mix over doughballs.
Melt butter; let cool 10 minutes, then pour over doughballs.
Put a towel over pan and let doughballs sit overnight.
Put in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: maple syrup
directions: Bring Karo, sugar and water to boil 5 to 10 minutes or until desired consistency.
Cool and add flavoring.

title: tropical cheese pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese and sugar with mixer until fluffy.
Add drained pineapple and 1/2 cup of nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread in pie shell.

title: caramel chocolate fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry cake mix, melted butter, chopped nuts and 1/3 c. evaporated milk.
Pour half of this mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan; bake for 6 minutes.
Meanwhile, put caramels and remaining evaporated milk into a heavy saucepan.
Heat and stir until caramels are melted and mixture is well blended.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips over baked layer, drizzle with caramel mixture, and top with remaining cake mixture, spreading evenly.
Return to oven and bake 15-18 minutes, or until top looks dry.
Cool and cut into fingers.

title: cajun hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Drop with a large spoon into hot oil in a deep fat fryer.
Cook until brown, turning with a long wooden spoon.
Great with fried catfish.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Wash and boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Peel and place in mixing bowl.
Mash and mix well with all other ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Cool and cut in desired size squares.

title: jackie's eggs-exptional brunch(serves 2)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Add oil to frypan.
Pour in mixture. When formed consistently, turn over, omelette style, to desired wellness.
Enjoy.

title: pumpkin potato bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add and mix 1 egg at a time.
Mix dry ingredients and add to sugar and eggs.
Add pumpkin, potatoes, oil, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 big loaves.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fill cupcake liners 1/2 full.
Top each with 1 tablespoon cream cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Peel cukes and slice thin.
Layer cukes in a medium size bowl. Cover with 3 cups water or enough to cover and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Chill.
Pour off salted water and rinse in clear water. Drain.
Blend sour cream, vinegar and sugar.
Fold into cukes. Serve with a sprinkling of salt and pepper.

title: best banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add beaten egg, lemon juice and well mashed bananas. Add flour with baking powder, salt and soda and then add the nuts. Turn into a greased loaf pan and bake in moderate oven at 350° until toothpick comes out mostly clean. This bread is wonderfully moist and full of flavor.

title: tater tot and beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Next layer onions.
Spread soup over onions.
Cover with shredded cheese and place Tater Tots, side by side, over cheese.
Sprinkle garlic powder over Tater Tots. Bake in moderately hot oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until Tater Tots are browned.

title: cheese vegie soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup water; add the rest of the water and mix in
all vegetables (frozen), onions and hash browns. Cover and simmer
minutes.
Add
cheese, milk and soup.
Stir over medium heat until all the cheese melts.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish
with
Durkee fried onion rings. Serve with warm croissants.

title: amaretto bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces and place in medium bowl.
Pour on half and half.
Cover bowl and let stand for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream margarine, 3/4 cup sugar and egg.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan with dough. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: delightful punch
directions: Mix lemonade Kool-Aid, sugar and water in punch bowl.
Add 5 Alive juice and ginger ale.
Mix cherry Kool-Aid according to directions and freeze into ice cubes.
Place cherry ice cubes in cups and pour punch into cups.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Blend together thoroughly.
Chill dough.
Remove from refrigerator and pinch off 24 balls of dough.
Press into tiny muffin pans.

title: frozen salad or dessert
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl; blend well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch container.
Put whatever is left in smaller container, such as a pretty mold.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter in a saucepan until tender.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir in bouillon dissolved in 2 cups hot water.
Cook until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in milk gradually.
Add seasonings and broccoli with cooking liquid, mixing well.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour sugar over cranberries.
Let stand overnight.
Stir sugar in cranberries until dissolved.

title: scalloped squash
directions: Squash should be cooked and mashed.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, 3/4 stick of oleo and sugar, then add squash.
Place squash mixture in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour and 1/4 stick oleo; sprinkle on top of squash.
Top with broken pecans.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Bring carrots to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Drain and put in a bowl to chill with bell peppers and onion
. In a saucepan, mix the remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil and cook 15 minutes.
Mix with carrot mixture.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour (but the longer the better) before serving.
Keeps well.

title: dirt cake(for kids)
directions: You will need 1 plastic flowerpot, 8-inches in diameter and 8-inches high.

title: mexicorn pudding
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Combine egg substitute and milk.
Add to corn mixture.
Stir to combine.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Place dish in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour hot water into pan (about 1-inch deep).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 6 (1/2 cup) servings, 95 calories per serving.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Beat butter at medium speed and add sugar, beating well. Add egg and molasses. Combine flour and next 4 ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with water, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix after each addition. Pour batter into a lightly greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Serve with whipped cream or lemon sauce.

title: bacon cheese rolls
directions: Trim crust from loaf bread.
Cut each slice into 1 inch strips (3 per slice).
Place on top of 1/2 slice bacon.
Squeeze a thread of cheese on top of bread.
Roll up and place a toothpick through to hold.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: fruit cups with pineapple cream dressing
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 tablespoon syrup for dressing recipe; set aside. Combine pineapple chunks and next 4 ingredients; toss gently. Spoon into individual serving dishes and top with Pineapple Cream Dressing. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: smoked oyster pate
directions: Drain oysters and puree in food processor or blender.
Add cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Mix in wine, mustard and sage.
Form into a ball shape.
Cover and chill overnight or until firm.
Combine walnuts and parsley.
Roll pate in mixture to coat. Serve with crackers or French bread.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except crackers.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes or longer at 250°.
When done, cover with crushed crackers.

title: joe's dietetic lasagna
directions: In a large frying pan, place oil, beef, pork, onions, and oregano and heat over medium heat until dark brown (killing all offensive critters)!
Drain excess fluids and place in large pot and pour in all of the red sauce.
After drinking some of the wine, pour remainder in sauce.
Stir and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes. In another large pot, fill approximately 1/2 way with water and add a little oil to keep pasta from sticking together.
Add a small dash of salt to keep your heart pumping.
Bring water to boil and place all of the lasagna noodles in pot and stir constantly so they don't stick together.
Cook noodles until almost tender and then remove and drain water.
Remove sauce from heat and ladle and coat bottom of large aluminum roasting pan.
Lay noodles in pan -- approximately 3 -4 noodles per layer.
Between each layer of noodles, spread additional red sauce and1/3 of the mozzarella and ricotta cheese (will not want to spread out evenly so just clump it.)
Repeat layering until it reaches top of pan.
Spread sauce on the top of the noodles and sprinkle parmesan cheese, thereby completing ordeal.
Place aluminum foil over pan.
Cook in preheated oven at 350 degrees for30 minutes.
Now remove cover and cook for additional 15 minutes at same temperature.
Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes.
Before eating take some Pepcid.
Enjoy!!

title: favorite coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease two 9 inch cake pans. Heat butter with milk until melted.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
In a mixing bowl, beat 4 eggs until thick and light. Add sugar gradually and continue beating until smooth and thick. Stir in grated lemon rind and juice.
Mix in flour gently and gradually.
Stir in the warm milk; mix.
Pour batter into pans and bake 30 minutes.
While cake bakes, make the filling.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix first ingredients; add beaten eggs, then stir in zucchini, oil, milk and nuts.
Mix until moistened. May have to add more flour.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: apple-carrot bake
directions: Combine carrots and water; bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes until crisp and tender.
Drain and set aside.
Combine sugar and flour; set aside.
Layer half the carrots and apples in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half sugar and flour mixture; dot with butter.
Repeat procedure.
Drizzle with orange juice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Toss before serving.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix crumbs with melted butter and press into an 8-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter until just clear. Spread into crust.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, dry milk, cornstarch, cocoa and salt.
Add egg yolks and water.
Cook until thick.
Remove from stove.
Add vanilla, cover and let set 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and pile on chocolate.
Brown.

title: coconut d-lite
directions: Crush the crackers. Melt the oleo.
Mix.
(Reserve 1/2 cup cracker mixture for top.)
Mix the pudding and the milk.
Mix in the ice cream.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been lined with cracker mixture.
Spread with the Cool Whip.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Allow to set until the consistency of egg white, then whip.
Add crushed pineapple, whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Pour into molds.
When congealed, serve on lettuce leaf and garnish with fresh raspberries, if desired.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Drain pineapple, dissolve gelatine in heated pineapple juice. In same sauce pan add cranberries.
Mix well.
Add pineapple, oranges, and pecans.
Pour in ring mold or dish and refrigerate.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, melt butter in pan.
Heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with fork only until flour leaves side of bowl.
Turn out on board and knead until smooth. Roll out into rectangle 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon on apples.
Spread apples on dough.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Slice dough 1/2 inch thick and put in melted butter in pan.
Pour sugared water over that and bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Start oven at 400°. Turn to 350°. Bake slowly for 1 hour at 300°.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together hash browns, tossed with salt and pepper and butter.
Mix together with soup and sour cream.
Top with cornflakes mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cherry crumb
directions: Pour pie filling in baking dish. Sprinkle cake mix on top. Next, chip butter on top. Sprinkle top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 min.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook and stir onions and green pepper in margarine until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, paprika, mustard and pepper.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk gradually. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, boil and stir one minute. Stir in corn and eggs.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix crumbs and melted margarine, sprinkle over corn.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until bubbly; approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: italian casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Rinse and drain.
In skillet over low heat, brown sausage and onions.
Drain.
In mixing bowl, toss together noodles, sausage, onions, mushrooms, 1 3/4 cups cheese (Cheddar or Mozzarella) and pizza sauce.
Put in casserole.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and remaining cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, and salt; gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°F for 8 - 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies will be soft.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack. Cool completely.

title: round steak morrelli
directions: Cut the steak into 6 portions.
Combine the flour and salt and sprinkle 2 tablespoons of mixture over the steak.
Pound the mixture into both sides of the steak.
In a skillet, heat the shortening and brown the meat.
Transfer meat to 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Blend remaining flour mixture to pan drippings. Stir in remaining ingredients constantly until thick and bubbly. Pour the mixture over meat and cover dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until the meat is tender.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer vegetables, soup and cheese, vegetables, soup and cheese.
Top with cheese and microwave for 8 minutes on High.
Top with one can fried onion rings and microwave for 2 minutes.

title: warm string bean salad
directions: In a small bowl combine the vinegar and lemon juice.
Whisk in the mustard, salt and pepper to taste; then whisk in the oil in a thin stream.
Add the garlic and season with additional salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy cheese bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix, cheese and poppy seed.
Add egg and milk; mix well.
Mix 1 minute.
Turn into a well-greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle additional poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool.
Serve warm.

title: festive mints
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at high speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Knead until smooth. Shape mints into rubber candy molds and place on paper towel covered baking sheet. Cover with another paper towel and let stand overnight to harden.
Yields 8 1/2 to 9 dozen mints.

title: crab mousse(dip)
directions: Melt cream cheese and soup in top of double boiler.
Add celery, green onions and mayonnaise; stir very well.
Drain crab and add to mixture.
Dissolve one package Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup boiling water and add to mixture in pan.
Add Old Bay, salt and pepper.
Pour in bowl and chill.
Serve as a dip with small crackers such as Sociables, wheat crackers, etc.
(Old Bay can be found at speciality stores.)

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine all ingredients together and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add beans, sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook for a few minutes.
Pour in baking dish; add drained macaroni.
Stir with fork.
Place strips of cheese on top. Put in oven until cheese gets hot.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown the ground beef in Dutch oven. Drain fat.
Return pan to medium-low heat and add remaining ingredients. Cook, stirring occasionally.
After 20 minutes, remove from heat.
Allow to cool and store in a jar in the refrigerator.
Reheat to serve over hot dogs!
Yields about 4 cups of chili.

title: green veggie soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Bring broth to boil.
Add other ingredients, vegetable last.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.
Combine crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Drop by rounded tablespoons 3 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
DO NOT OVERBAKE.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove cookies to foil to cool completely.

title: mexican dip
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch pan, layer each ingredient in above order. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 with nacho chips.

title: schnitzel beans
directions: Fry bacon until brown and crisp.
Chop in small pieces.
Add sugar and vinegar to bacon and grease.
Cook until sugar is dissolved; add green beans and simmer about 20 minutes.
Add chopped onion and serve.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Blend together the bread crumbs, parsley, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Dip skinned chicken in melted butter and roll in crumb mixture.
Cook 35 minutes at 350°, covered, or until tender and 35 minutes, open, at 350°.
Store unused portions in refrigerator or freezer.

title: orange ball cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut.
Save some powdered sugar to roll balls in after rolling in coconut.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Cut up chicken; salt, pepper and dash of red pepper.
Fry to a golden brown.
Lower heat and add chopped celery, bell pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add the sausage and rice to chicken and chopped vegetables.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Add (5 cups) and 1 chopped garlic clove.
Stir and cover.
Do not stir anymore.
Let simmer over heat for 1 hour.
Keep covered and serve hot.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Melt cream cheese and margarine together in double boiler. Stir in vanilla and add enough powdered sugar to thicken (approximately 1 to 1 1/2 box).
Spread between halved graham crackers.

title: frozen pumpkin mousse
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, milk, ginger (chopped fine) and seasonings thoroughly.
Blend in cognac and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream. Turn into a 2-quart mold and freeze overnight.
Garnish with whipped cream if desired.

title: cherry-nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquids.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 3 small loaves.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and mix into a ball after it has chilled. Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut; cook carrots for 2 minutes.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Let set overnight.

title: melting moments
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil vegetable oil, butter and sugar for 2 minutes.
Use a jelly roll pan with graham cracker squares. (Do not use a cookie sheet.)
Avoid crushing the crackers.
Pour sugar mix over crackers.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over each cracker top.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pull apart and cool.

title: quick chili with rice
directions: Spray a 12-inch skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Add turkey; cook until no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Stir in chili powder; cook 1 minute.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, beans, tomato juice, water, dried onion, salt, cumin, oregano, pepper, garlic powder and rice.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Garnish with sliced green onion, if desired.

title: bacon wraparounds
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Crush 8 more cookies for topping.

title: congealed "green goddess" salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool. Add 1 cup pineapple juice.
Add water, if necessary, to make 1 cup.
Mix well with cottage cheese, cream cheese, pineapple, dressing, pimentos and cucumber.
Pour into shallow dish with cover and refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: tamale pie
