directions: Cook meat in skillet until brown. Add chopped onion, creamed corn, tomatoes and olives. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix the yellow corn meal with the milk. Add to mixture.
Stir and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add to the corn mixture.
Stir.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 300° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Spread each breast with 1 tablespoon of green chilies.
Place 1 cheese strip on top of each portion of chilies.
Roll up each chicken breast and tuck ends under.

Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, chili powder, salt, cumin and pepper in a shallow dish. Dip each breast into melted butter and in bread crumb mixture. Place breast in baking dish, seam-side down.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook potato and onion until tender.
Cook beef and drain grease.
Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: sweet pickles(bread and butter)
directions: Put cukes, onions, peppers and garlic in a large container. Cover with ice; mix several times.
Allow to stand 3 hours.
(Same thing can be accomplished by refrigeration of cukes overnight before slicing.)
Drain well; combine remaining ingredients and pour over the cukes.
Heat just to a boil; seal in hot jars, or chill and serve.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in a bowl.
Butter must be at room temperature.
Work with hands to form a ball (no crumbs).
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prick with a fork. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove and cut into squares.
Return to oven at 275° for 25 minutes. Take out and enjoy!

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown beef and onions in skillet.
Add tomato soup, water and seasonings.
Add corn and green pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Put in greased baking dish.
Cover with your favorite corn bread mix and brown.

title: canned sliced cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and soak overnight in salt water. Drain the next morning.
Weaken vinegar with a
water and bring to a boil.
Drop sliced cucumbers in and bring to a second boil.
Pack in hot jars and pour hot vinegar over and then seal. When ready to use, drain vinegar and use a sour cream dressing.

title: crunchy party mix
directions: In a saucepan, mix margarine, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and pepper sauce.
Heat and stir until margarine melts.
In a large roasting pan, mix pretzels, cereals and nuts.
Drizzle margarine mixture over cereal mixture; toss to coat.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in oil with onion, garlic and parsley.
Add tomato paste, 2 cups water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add lasagna to 6 quarts boiling water (salted), stirring often to prevent sticking until tender.
Drain; mix eggs and cottage cheese. Arrange lasagna in baking dish in layers of sauce and slices of cheese.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: snowball salad
directions: Optional:
Use can of drained fruit cocktail.

title: tropical garden cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat shortening, butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add egg and orange peel; blend well.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with orange juice.

title: cider apple crisp
directions: Work together brown and white sugars, flour, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg until crumbly.
Spread apples in greased baking pan or dish.
Pour cider over apples and spread mixture over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: homemade soup(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker (crock-pot); cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours.
Remove bones before serving.

title: bread crumb encrusted pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash and trim fat off the tenderloin and place in a Ziploc bag.
In a small bowl, combine oil, salt, pepper, rosemary, garlic and parsley.
Stir and pour over the pork into the Ziploc bag.
Let stand for 1 to 2 hours or overnight.
Place pork in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs, covering all sides.
Place in oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until bread crumbs brown and inside the pork is slightly pink in color and juices run clear.
Allow to cool for 5 minutes before cutting. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat shortening in milk until shortening is melted.
Add sugar and allow to cool until warm. Beat in egg and yeast mixture.
Add flour, one cup at a time; knead lightly.
Pinch off desired number of rolls or make into 2 loaves.
Place rolls or bread into well-greased pans; allow to rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: fridge rolls(keeps indefinitely)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, salt, sugar and egg (beaten lightly).
Add 1/2 of flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add rest of flour; blend until smooth.
Cover.
Let rise at room temperature until double in size.

title: "goop"(broccoli-rice casserole)
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onions, peppers and celery in butter (margarine).
Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine with cheese, soup and mushrooms.
Fold in cooked rice.
Use a 3-quart casserole.
Can refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pie crust
directions: In bowl, cut up shortening, flour and salt until mixture is beaded.
Add beaten egg, ice water and vinegar.
Pull mixture together with pastry mixer (or fork).
Knead just to get in a ball.
Place in refrigerator for easy handling.

title: world's greatest potatoes
directions: Cut the potatoes into cubes.
Combine butter and Parmesan cheese and pour over the potatoes and toss well and put into microwave-safe dish and microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Or bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour. Add Cheddar cheese and bacon bits and microwave or bake until melted.

title: egg mcpennington
directions: Split English muffin and toast lightly.
If I am in a hurry, I do not toast.
Place half a slice of cheese on each side.
Add turkey bacon and cooked egg white.
Put halves together.
If you want to take it with you, wrap it up and microwave later for about 30 seconds.
The cheese will melt and it is great.
It does not have as much as the competitive brand.

title: best ever turkey
directions: Wash and clean turkey.
Season to taste.
Place apple, onion, potato, carrot and celery inside bird.
Place in a roasting pan large enough to cover (or cover tightly with foil).
Add 3 quarts water in roasting pan; cover, bring to a boil and boil 15 minutes. Place in preheated oven (475°) for 45 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave in oven to steam overnight.
Do not open oven door until morning.
Turkey will be browned and moist.
Lots of broth for dressing and soups.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook beef and chili powder until browned.
Spoon off fat. Stir in soup, pepper, corn, salsa and water.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions; spoon evenly over soup mixture.
Bake 25 minutes in 400°
oven.

title: pea casserole
directions: Drain peas.
Pour juice into pan.
Add butter and flour; thicken.
Put peas in baking dish.
Pour juice on peas.
Cover peas with chopped, hard-boiled eggs, then crackers, then cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Combine all ingredients, except fried onions, in a large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with fried onions in the last 2 or 3 minutes of baking time.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar, salt, peanuts and Karo syrup into a large Pyrex glass bowl and cook on Full power for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 3 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and cook for 2 minutes. Remove and add baking soda.
Blend well and quickly pour into greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break.

title: ruth's whole wheat rolls - master mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients until well blended.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like corn meal.
Store in cool dry place in container with tight fitting lid.
Will keep 8 weeks not refrigerated, much longer in refrigerator or freezer.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken (or turkey). Pull off bones. Saute onion and celery in oleo. Mix all ingredients; add chicken last. Put in greased crock-pot. Cook on high 45 minutes, then turn to low and cook 4 hours or until done. May need to stir.

title: microwave onion soup
directions: In a 3-quart microwave-safe dish, combine butter and onions and saute on Medium-high for 10 minutes or until onions are tender. Stir once.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the oil and sugar. Add eggs and pumpkin. Add dry ingredients and nuts. Add water.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread loaves overnight in refrigerator, but do not allow to rise.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear 1 loaf into pieces and drop at random into pan.
Melt butter and add the remaining ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Pour over the torn bread in the pan.
Tear the second loaf of bread and place over the ingredients in the pan (filling the empty spots).
Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes and turn onto waxpaper.
If desired nuts or raisins may be added to the topping.

title: chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Coat a wok or large skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat pan at medium-high (325°) for 2 minutes.
Add chicken and stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes (until meat is lightly browned).
Add vegetables and 1/2 cup of the broth. Cover and cook 1 1/2 minutes.

title: dixie's pecan log
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients, then mix in sugar gradually. Knead with hands as mixture becomes stiff.
Knead until smooth. Divide into two 10-inch logs.
Cover with a damp cloth and chill several hours or overnight.

title: kay's lettuce and cauliflower salad
directions: Tear lettuce and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Put in bowl in layers with onion.
Mix the mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Pour over top of salad.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Best to put dressing over 1 hour before serving.
May refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: applesauce loaf cake
directions: Mix and sift together flour, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, ground cloves, salt and soda.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually; continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg. Beat well.
Stir in applesauce.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched with fingertips.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Top with lemon flavored frosting or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Excellent warm or cold.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix
together
the
ground beef, salt, pepper, milk and oatmeal.
Form
into balls or patties and brown in frying pan. Place
meat
mixture
into
a
baking
pan.
Mix
together the catsup,
brown
sugar,
vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Bring
to
a boil, remove from heat; pour over the meat balls. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the shortening and peanut butter. Add sugars slowly and cream well. Add egg, milk and vanilla. Beat well. Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Mix well. Shape by rounded teaspoonful into balls. Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and place candy Kiss on top of each cookie, pressing so that cookie cracks around edges.
Return to oven and bake for 2 to 5 minutes more. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pecan-cheese crispies
directions: Combine cheese and butter in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer and blend.
Add hot sauce and mustard. Gradually add flours, mixing until blended.
Stir in cereal. Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased baking sheets and flatten with a fork, making a crisscross design.
Press a pecan half in the center of each cookie. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken jacqueline
directions: Melt all together and pour over boneless chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tea punch
directions: Combine; makes 2 quarts.

title: chicken superb
directions: Skin chicken breasts.
Coat chicken in flour and cracker crumbs.
Melt butter in large skillet and put in casserole dish. Put in same skillet off of chicken; add mushrooms and brown, then add celery soup.
Heat until gravy-like.
Pour over chicken.

title: white sauce butter balls
directions: Line 2 baking sheets with wax paper. Set aside.
In a sifter, combine flour, salt and white pepper.
Sift into a large bowl. Use an electric mixer to cream in the butter or margarine until smooth.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto prepared baking sheets.
Place in freezer until butter balls are frozen. Remove frozen balls from baking sheets.
Place in a firm freezer container with a tight fitting lid or in 1 or 2 heavy-duty plastic bags.
Label the container or plastic bags with date and contents. Return them back to the freezer.
Use within 6 months. Makes about 28 white sauce butter balls.

title: irish oatmeal bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan (9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch).
Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix egg, honey and milk in medium bowl using rotary beater.
Pour egg mixture into flour.
Beat mixture.
Stir with wooden spoon until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Spread batter into loaf pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes until top is crusty and toothpick comes out clean from center.
Turn onto rack.
Brush with margarine.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix.
Roll into balls and then roll in finely chopped walnuts. Chill.
Make approximately 3 to 4 days before using and chill. Flavors better if it sits a few days.
Don't wrap in plastic as walnuts will become soggy. Use aluminum foil.
Serve on crackers.

title: beef stew ragout style
directions: In a medium saucepan, brown beef in oil.
Add onion, garlic, saute until onion is soft.
Add water and tomato paste.
Stir until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover, simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar together.
Set aside.
Combine bourbon and corn syrup in a bowl; stir in cocoa mixture, pecans, and vanilla wafers.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls; dip each in egg white and roll in chocolate sprinkles.
Store in a covered container.
Yield: 1 1/2 dozen.

title: frozen chocolate charlotte
directions: Split ladyfingers but do not separate into individual pieces. Brush flat surfaces with liqueur.
Line sides of 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers, rounded sides against pan.
Separate remaining ladyfingers and line bottom of pan, overlapping to fit. Melt chocolate in top of double boiler, stirring.
Dissolve coffee in boiling water and cool.
Beat egg yolks in small bowl at high speed until foamy.
Beat in sugar gradually; continue beating until thick.
Beat in vanilla, coffee and melted chocolate.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Stir one cup of egg white in chocolate and then fold chocolate mixture into remaining egg whites.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pan and freeze.
Garnish with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese crackers.

title: red cake
directions: Makes 3 layers.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: carrot dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk, carrots and parsley.
Stir until flour is moist.
Drop dumplings into simmering liquid in approximately 8 mounds (chicken or beef stock may be used).
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes without lifting cover.
Serves 8 people.

title: two way cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars.
Add egg yolks to water; add vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda and add to first mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Pat out on cookie sheet. Cover dough with chocolate chips; Pat down.
Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Cover chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cut in squares.

title: tomato soup
directions: Peel and chop the tomatoes.
Saute in butter until tender. Mix tomatoes with chicken stock and simmer 20 minutes.
Run the mixture through a food blender and strain to remove seeds.
Add the half and half and a pat of butter.
Mix together and heat for about 5 minutes.
Soup may be sweetened with a bit of sugar to remove the tartness of the tomatoes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese ball 2
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Put all ingredients with the exception of the pecans into a mixer and mix well. Refrigerate until firm.
Roll into a ball and roll in pecans until well coated.
Wrap in foil or plastic and let ripen in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
Leave at room temperature for 2 hours before serving.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: mexican salad bowl
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cover and chill. Combine corn, beans, olives and shredded lettuce.
Toss with dressing.
Serves 6.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Shred
cabbage	and
slice
celery (by hand or electric food processor).
Parboil shredded cabbage and sliced celery 5 minutes in
large	saucepan,
until
crispy
tender;
drain. Combine with
soup, marjoram and horseradish in buttered 1 to 1 1/2
quart casserole.	Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes
at 375° or until mixture is bubbly and crumbs are golden brown.

title: three week slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, onions and pepper into a large bowl.
Mix sugar and 2 cups vinegar and pour over the vegetables.
Combine 1 cup vinegar, oil, celery seed and salt in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over the first mixture.
Cover and refrigerate three weeks before serving.

title: easy supper
directions: In an ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass dish, layer raw hamburger meat, raw potatoes (thinly sliced), salt and pepper.
Repeat layers until the dish is full.
Top with soup.
Cover and cook at 400° until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Prepare butter crunch from recipe below.
Heat oven to 450°. In ungreased 9-inch pie pan or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, mix pie filling, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1 cup of the butter crunch evenly on top.
Bake 10 minutes or until top is lightly golden and bubbly.

title: lela's spring pea salad
directions: Rinse frozen peas in hot water.
Drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.
Mix dressing, mustard and garlic together.
Pour over salad mixture.
Toss lightly.
Chill.

title: peanut butter tassies
directions: Slice cookie dough 3/4 inch thick.
Then quarter each slice. Place 1 quarter in each "mini" muffin pan (ungreased).
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
They will puff! Place 1 candy on each and allow to melt slightly.
Use a toothpick to smooth ridges of candies.

title: cranberry apple stuffing
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onion and celery, stirring often, until cooked tender.
Add to croutons and mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stuff bird or spoon into casserole dish.
Makes enough for 14 to 16 pound birds.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Skim fat off broth.
Saute onion, celery and garlic in fat. Add broth, soup, chicken and peppers to onion and heat.
Correct seasoning.
In buttered casserole, arrange layers of tortillas, chicken sauce and cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until it bubbles.
Serves 8.

title: peach preserves
directions: Select any variety
of
white
or
yellow peach of good dessert quality and firm ripe stage.

title: raw apple cake
directions: In bowl, put apples, sugar, oil, eggs, walnuts, cinnamon, soda and salt; stir to mix well.
Add flour, small amounts at a time, stir each time.
After mixed well, put in oiled baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hot shrimp dip supreme
directions: Put all ingredients in container and place in hot water about 1 hour before time to use or until cheese is soft.
Fold lightly together.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: corn puddin'
directions: Place corn in mixing bowl.
Stir in salt, pepper, slightly beaten eggs, milk and melted butter (also sugar if desired).
When mixed well, pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 350° until firm.

title: marinated brisket
directions: Place brisket on a rack in a large, covered, baking pan.
Mix, in a small bowl, garlic salt, celery salt, onion salt, black pepper, liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce.
Using a pastry brush, brush the marinade onto the brisket. Bake in a slow oven at 325° for about 4 to 5 hours.
Let cool and slice.
Drain the juice from pan and chill.
Remove fat and use juice over meat when it is reheated.

title: mom's best sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Chill, make into balls the size of walnuts or larger.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove bones and skin from chicken and cook.
Break chicken into pieces to cover bottom of casserole dish.
Mix the soup and the sour cream together (a little milk may be added, if needed); pour over chicken.
Mix the dressing mix as directed on package and spread over the chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breaded shrimp
directions: Clean deveined shrimp; try to save tail.
Split down back to tail; press shrimp flat.
Sprinkle shrimp with Tony's seasoning. Dip in crumbs, then egg mixture, then crumbs.
Press to secure crumbs.
Let chill.
Drop in deep oil; drain.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Mix and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour this boiling hot liquid over the cucumbers in jars.
Place cap on jars, screwing band tight. Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.

title: bacon and cheese panada
directions: Partially fry bacon and drain.
Beat eggs with soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Fold in bread crumbs and cheese.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in medium oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Ten minutes before casserole is done, arrange bacon slices on top.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, syrup and beaten eggs.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch plain pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Cook meat; drain.
Add taco mix; mix well.
Heat beans. Spread beans in casserole dish.
Cover with meat.
Pour soup to within 1 inch of side of dish.
Sprinkle cheese and melt. Sprinkle with onions.
Place sour cream in middle top.
Arrange chips around edge.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts evenly in bottom.
Pour chocolate mixture into shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until filling is firm.

title: iowa preacher's casserole
directions: Brown beef with chopped onion and green pepper.
Mix soups together, then add all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole. Sprinkle noodles on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: chicken en mole poblano
directions: Heat a shallow layer of oil in a very large skillet, or use 2 skillets.
Brown chicken in oil on both sides, then add water to cover and simmer 30 minutes.
While chicken cooks, make sauce by placing all remaining ingredients (except bay leaf) in a blender and processing until smooth.
When chicken is done, drain broth and add 1 1/2 cups of broth to sauce.
Blend, pour over chicken in skillet, add bay leaf, and cook on low heat for 35 more minutes. Serve with rice.
Serves 8. Turkey may be used instead of chicken.

title: black forest torte
directions: Separate filling and cherries.
Separate cherries into 2 bowls, 1/2 each.
Reserve 1 bowl for top.

title: cheezy spinach bake
directions: Drain spinach, squeezing out excess liquid.
Combine all ingredients and pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine oleo, sugar and pudding mix in large bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs, gradually add flour mixture, then add oats and raisins or nuts. Will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: date cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water.
Cook onions in milk in microwave or top of double boiler until soft.
Cook parsley in butter (can also be done in microwave).
Add flour; stir well. Combine with milk and potatoes.
Stir until smooth.
Add salt and pepper.

title: purple junk dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bananas can be dipped in lemon juice first, before adding to other ingredients to keep from browning.
Keep refrigerated.
Can be topped with Cool Whip.

title: perfect banana pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt. Stir in milk, beaten eggs and vanilla. Cook in double boiler until thick. Alternate layering sliced bananas and wafers, then pour sauce over. Can top with wafers or you can make meringue.

title: michelle's favorite
directions: Mix together macaroni, hamburger, peas and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
For the last 5 minutes of baking, put cheese slices on top.

title: smoothest southern pound cake
directions: Beat softened butter at medium speed with electric mixer (about 2 minutes) until creamy.
Gradually add 3 cups sugar, beating at medium speed, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine cake flour and baking soda; add to butter mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at lower speed, just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake in 10-inch Bundt pan at 300° for 2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean or bake in two 9 x 5-inch pans for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: kolachi
directions: Allow butter and cream cheese to soften. Cream together butter and cream cheese; add eggs and mix well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a bowl until blended, but not fluffy. Add eggs, salt, syrup and pecan pieces.
Pour into pie shell. Top with pecan halves and bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and eggs.
Pour into hot cooking oil in a small stream, beginning in center of pan and widening circle to form an area about the size of a paper plate.
Turn and brown top side.
Remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy barbecue spareribs
directions: Put spareribs in crock-pot.
Cover with 1/2 bottle of barbecue sauce.
Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours.
When spareribs are tender, put on grill for 5 minutes each side to crisp.
Coat with extra barbecue sauce for extra flavor.

title: marianneo country ham rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ham, relish and mayonnaise.
Split each party roll and spread with butter or margarine.
Place teaspoon of ham mixtures on each roll.
Bake on cookie sheet 8 minutes or until hot.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal and water over a low fire until water is cooked down.
Add milk, oil, eggs and onion.
Mix in all dry ingredients with the cornmeal mixture.
Drop spoonfuls into 375° oil and fry until crispy, golden brown.
Drain and serve immediately.

title: hot fruit punch
directions: Heat 2 cups juice and dissolve sugar in it.
Add Jell-O and dissolve. Add all other juices and mix well.
Heat almost to boiling point and serve hot.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Put layer of batter in bottom of tube pan. Add 1/2 cranberry sauce and spread evenly. Add rest of batter and put rest of cranberry on top. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Remove from pan after 5 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown burger and add taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
Cut up all salad fixings, mix in hamburger, put dressing on to taste at serving time.
Crush Dorito's and add to salad.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Put half the peppers and the hot pepper in blender container and process on high speed until liquified.
Pour into saucepan. Do remainder of peppers.
Add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Add pectin, stirring.
Pour into sterilized glasses and seal with paraffin.
Makes 4 to 6 glasses.
Serve on crackers or cream cheese.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Saute onions, garlic and parsley in butter.
Add oysters and cook until oysters are well plumped.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour into a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, until heated thoroughly.
Serves four.

title: skyline's apple muffins
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
In another bowl, combine buttermilk, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Add milk mixture to sugar mixture alternately with flour; mix well after each addition.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Pour into muffin pan and sprinkle with sugar, combined with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Yield:
About 15 muffins.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, marshmallows, oleo and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat to a boil; mixture should be bubbling all over top.
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until completely melted. Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan; cool.
Cut into 30 pieces.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cover chicken with water; add salt, pepper, celery, bay leaf and onion. Cook chicken until done. Remove meat from chicken; put broth and chicken in refrigerator to cool. Remove chicken. Skim fat off of broth. Add chicken, onion, carrots, bouillon cubes and parsley. Simmer until carrots are tender.
Add noodles. When noodles are tender, soup is ready.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together, adding sour cream last.
Bake in casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bachelor's stir-fry
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; set aside.
Dice chicken into 1-inch cubes; place in bowl with soy sauce and ginger.
Mix; let sit for 5 minutes.
In large skillet or wok, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add chicken; stir until cooked on all sides.
Remove chicken.
Add 1 tablespoon oil and diced onion; fry until translucent (kind of clear).
Add vegetables; stir-fry.
Add chicken; stir-fry.
Add stir-fry sauce; stir for 30 to 40 seconds. Serve over rice.

title: zucchini-ham-cheese pie with crumb topping
directions: Saute onion, zucchini and garlic in oil in large skillet about 5 minutes or until tender and crisp.
Remove skillet from heat, add ham, Swiss cheese, sour cream, dill weed, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into pie crust.
Melt butter in small skillet, stir in bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese with a fork.
Sprinkle mixture in a 2-inch band around edge leaving center open.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with parsley and tomato wedges if so desired.

title: prize winning danish puff
directions: Measure first cup of flour into bowl; cut in 1/2 cup butter. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water; mix with fork.
Round into ball; divide in half.
Pat into 2 strips, 12 x 3 inches.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool.
Cut up in cubes.
Cook broccoli and line bottom of dish.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, milk, cheese, lemon juice and curry powder.
Mix in chicken.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with 1/2 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in oven at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together well. Add vanilla, salt and skim milk. Spread bread and raisins in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with custard mixture. Let stand for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon. Place in pan of hot water. Bake at 350° until knife in center comes out clean.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, flour, vanilla and nuts together. Roll into balls. Bake at 350° (10 to 12 minutes). Cool and then roll into sugar.

title: best-ever meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup with the meat, saltines, egg, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Firmly shape mixture into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Remove meat to platter.
Keep warm.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons drippings from pan.
Stir remaining soup and water into drippings in pan, scraping up brown bits from bottom.
Over medium heat, heat soup mixture until hot, stirring constantly.
Serve this gravy with meat loaf.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange pineapple slices on brown sugar.
Place maraschino cherries in center of pineapple slices.

title: betsy mccall's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until barley tender.
Do not overcook.
Make white sauce of melted margarine, flour, onion, mustard and milk. Cook slowly until thick.
Remove from fire and add 2/3 of grated cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole and cover with cheese. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Reheat at serving time.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: potato torte
directions: Boil and mash potatoes; set aside.
Cook Italian sausage and cut into small pieces; set aside.
Saute onion in butter until transparent and add flour, Season-All salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Add the milk slowly, stirring constantly until it comes to a full boil. Sauce will be quite thin.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Punch with thumb.
Add strawberry jam (or variety of jam is pretty).
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: *raisin nut stuffing("bucuvala")
directions: Brown butter in a large pot.
Over low heat, add bread and mix very well until bread is browned.
Add drained raisins, walnuts, apples, vanilla, sugar and salt. Add orange juice gradually until slightly moistened. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes for flavors to blend, stirring often.
Serve with chicken or turkey.

title: baked chicken breasts(microwave)
directions: Split chicken breasts and skin, if desired.
Spray glass baking dish with nonstick/nonfat spray.
Weigh chicken and pour small amount of vinegar over chicken. Sprinkle with garlic powder and basil. Cover pan with waxed paper, piercing for vent.
Cook for 10 minutes per pound in microwave at maximum power.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 3 or 4 teaspoons of mixture to a mug filled with hot water.
Especially good on a cold winter evening.

title: cauliflower and bacon salad(serves 12; refrigerates up to 14 hours)
directions: In large bowl, layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon. Combine remaining ingredients and spread over salad.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Toss before serving.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine orange juice and cornstarch; mix well.
Stir in chicken.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Drain chicken; discard mixture.
Combine broth and soy sauce; set aside.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Put into dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Let cream cheese soften and mix with powdered sugar, then spread on first layer.
Mix each pudding with amount of milk called for on each package.
Pour over last layer and chill overnight.
Spread Cool Whip over top and serve.

title: french onion soup(serves 5)
directions: Saute onions in butter and bacon fat until brown.
Add broth, water and pepper to taste.
Cook on high heat for 5 minutes. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Pour into 5 ovenproof bowls. Float a slice of toast in each.
Sprinkle the cheese on top; brown for a few minutes under broiler.

title: oriental pasta and chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together mayonnaise, soy sauce, ginger and pepper until smooth.
Add macaroni, chicken, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, snow peas, green onions and red or green pepper. Toss well to coat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or until well chilled.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Boil lasagne and boil spinach.
Layer: spaghetti sauce, lasagne, spinach, cottage cheese, spaghetti sauce.
Last, top with cubed Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for Christmas colors.

title: miracle dessert(fruit cocktail cake)
directions: Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes or less until well blended. Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan coated with cooking spray or grease and flour.

title: mother's chocolate pie
directions: Add sugar to cocoa and mix.
Add egg yolks, milk, flour and salt.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens.
Add vanilla and margarine.

title: noodle cookies
directions: Put last 2 ingredients
into double boiler and melt chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Add noodles and mix well.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoon.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Put oil in pan you are baking in and place in oven.
Mix all other ingredients.
Mix hot oil with mixture.
Bake at 450° or 475° until brown.

title: massie stack cake
directions: Mix thoroughly the flour, salt, soda and baking powder by sifting together 3 times.
Cream shortening, then add sugar, a little at a time, blending well.
Add sorghum and mix thoroughly. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
To this, add flour and milk alternately and beat until smooth.
Place mixture, 3/8-inch thick, in floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes.
This should make 6 layers.
When cool, stack up layers, using applesauce generously between each layer.

title: cheese souffle sandwiches
directions: Soften butter and cheese. Beat with mixer until fluffy. Add Tabasco, onion powder, dill weed, Beau Monde seasoning and Lea & Perrins sauce and mix well. Remove crusts from bread. (Dry cut off crusts and put through food processor and save in freezer for homemade crumbs.) Spread 3 slices with mixture and stack. Spread slices and sides and cut into 4 or 6 pieces. Spread cut sides. Place on wax paper and freeze. Then place in plastic bags to store in freezer. When ready to use, place on well-greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° until edges are lightly browned. Makes about 60 pieces.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and mix with thawed potatoes.
Add sour cream, soup, cheese, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into a large greased casserole.
Mix corn flakes and remaining stick of butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rolled oat biscuits(for older babies and toddlers)
directions: Mix oatmeal, baking powder and salt.
Stir in margarine.
Stir in liquid to make a stiff dough.
Roll dough and cut into rounds. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Store tightly covered.

title: cajun roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a shallow baking pan, blend all ingredients except potatoes, mixing well.
Add potatoes and turn to coat each piece thoroughly.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and brown.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, melt morsels and butter.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk, vanilla and egg.
Pour into prepared pan. Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool before cutting.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Mix together gently, cottage cheese, sour cream and cooked noodles.
Add onion, garlic and seasonings.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Lay out on shallow baking pan.
Salt lightly and add lemon pepper.
Turn and do other side.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until done next to the bone.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with margarine.
Pour in mixture and top with dry Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill before serving.

title: oven art
directions: Combine flour and salt in large, flat-bottomed bowl.
Mix well with spoon.
Add water, mixing as you pour.
Knead 7 to 10 minutes until dough has smooth, firm consistency.
Place dough in a plastic bag to prevent drying.
(Do not use self-rising flour.) You can roll out the dough and cut out cookie-cutter shapes or mold dough into sculptures.
You can make Christmas decorations, baskets, lettering or anything else you can think of.

title: chocolate pudding delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (325° for Pyrex).
Cool completely.

title: peaches 'n' cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of 10-inch pie pan.
Combine in large mixing bowl, the flour, baking powder, salt, pudding mix, softened butter, egg and milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan.
Place well-drained peach slices over batter.
In small mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons reserved peach syrup.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon mixture to within 1-inch of side of pan.
For topping, combine 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1/2 to 1 teaspoon of cinnamon; sprinkle over cream cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown. Filling will be soft.
Chill well before serving and store in the refrigerator.

title: pizza popcorn
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan over medium heat; stir in oregano, garlic salt, basil and red pepper flakes.
Heat 1 minute. Pour over popped corn in large bowl; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Toss lightly until coated.

title: hershey pie
directions: *If a more chocolatey taste is desired, increase chocolate bars according to taste.

title: marilyn's eggnog for a crowd
directions: Beat yolks with sugar until thick and lemony.
Slowly add brandy, rum and peach brandy.
Stir in milk and cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into eggnog.
Do not stir!
Top with freshly grated nutmeg.

title: chocolate wafer dessert
directions: Whip the cream and combine with powdered sugar and vanilla. Line a 9-inch pie pan with whole wafers, then bananas which have been sliced and top with whipped cream.
Repeat this one time. Top with crushed wafers.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.

title: stir-fried asparagus
directions: Rinse asparagus well; snap off tough ends.
Cut stems into thin diagonal slices, leaving tips whole (about 2 cups).
Cut celery into thin diagonal slices.
Heat oil in a large heavy frying pan or wok over medium-high heat.
Mix water, sugar, salt and ginger.
Stir into vegetables until liquid is nearly gone. Mix in bean sprouts and stir to mix with other vegetables.
Heat through, about 15 seconds.
Remove from heat and serve at once.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into molds; place into freezer.
When mixture is slushy, but not solid, place a stick in center.
Freeze solid.
Yields 1 serving.
Exchange:
1 fruit.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
ingredients.
Pour
into
9-inch unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° until done, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cajun fried chicken
directions: Remove giblets and necks, and rinse chickens with cold water. Drain cavities well; pat dry. Rub inside and outside of chickens with seasoning; set aside. Pour oil into a deep propane turkey fryer; heat to 350° according to manufacturer's instructions over medium-low flame. Place 1 chicken on fryer rod; carefully lower into hot oil. Fry 12 minutes or until a meat thermometer inserted in chicken breast registers 170°. (Keep oil temperature at 350°.) Remove from oil and drain. Repeat procedure for 2 remaining chickens. Cool slightly before serving.

title: cloud cake
directions: Mix ingredients for cake; bake by directions on cake mix box.

title: grilled turkey burgers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; form into 8 patties.
Chill 30 minutes.
Grill until done.
Baste with barbecue sauce while cooking, about 6 to 8 minutes on each side.
Place 1 slice of cheese on each patty during last minute or two of cooking.
Serve on buns with lettuce, tomato and other garnish of your choice. Yields 8 burgers.

title: old fashioned muffins
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg.
Add dry ingredients, milk and molasses.
Mix well.
Add raisins.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24 large muffins.

title: low-fat cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll bread dough out to rectangle 9 x 6-inch.
Spread skim milk over dough.
In small bowl combine cinnamon and brown sugar. Sprinkle over milk.
Roll up bread lengthways; seal seam with a little milk.
Cut 12 slices laying each pinwheel roll down flat in a 9 x 9-inch pan (sprayed with nonstick coating).
Cover.
Let rise in warm oven for 45 minutes (uncovered).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 375° oven.
One fat gram per roll.

title: creamy chocolate dessert
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Add partially cooled chocolate mixture; stir in flour.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator until chilled.

title: cocoa
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, dry milk and salt.
Gradually add water. Heat quickly to boiling.
Lower heat and cook slowly for 3 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 servings.

title: easy beef burgundy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in Burgundy. Add Kitchen Bouquet until soup mixture is as brown as desired (uncooked).
Place in a large baking pan or casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for about 2 hours or until tender.
Serve hot over buttered rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: tomato egg flower soup
directions: Soak mushrooms in warm water to cover for 30 minutes; drain and reserve 1 cup liquid.
Cut off and discard stems and dice caps.
Set aside.

title: sour cream oven breakfast cake
directions: Mix together nuts, 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; set aside. Cream sugar and butter together.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat well on slow speed.
Add vanilla.
Heavy batter is made.
Fold in sour cream.

title: tomato cakes
directions: Drain tomatoes.
Add beaten eggs and butter.
Add cracker crumbs; let stand for a few minutes.
If not stiff enough, add more cracker crumbs.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 350° until firm.
Cut in squares.
May also be used as a cake.
Fry at a very low heat.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: raspberry-cream tart
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
With hand, knead mixture until blended.
Pat pastry onto bottom and up side of a 10-inch tart pan with removable bottom.
Bake 20 minutes, or until pastry is golden.
In cup, beat egg white; use to brush hot pastry shell.
Cool pastry shell in pan on wire rack.
Remove side from pan.

title: pink peanut patties(microwave)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart glass bowl. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir and add raw peanuts.
Cook on High for 8 minutes.
Stir and add last 3 ingredients.
Beat until creamy and pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Break into pieces when firm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix white sugar and cinnamon together in a plastic bag or bowl.
Cut biscuits into 4 pieces and coat with sugar mixture. Spray tube pan with Pam and drop biscuit pieces into tube pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Melt margarine and brown sugar together, do not boil.
Pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Let stand 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all together.
Put in ice cream freezer and stir 5 to 10 minutes.
Look in to see if it is ready.

title: old-time tea cakes
directions: Mix together sugar and egg yolks, then add cream, soda and baking powder; blend well.
Add milk and butter; mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff and blend in.
Add enough flour to make stiff and roll out.
Cut and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 300° oven until brown.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Melt butter.
Add corn meal and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 250°.

title: everyday broccoli cheese chicken
directions: In skillet over medium heat, melt margarine; cook chicken 10 minutes, or until browned on both sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is tender and broccoli is done.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat ingredients for 2 minutes.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Stir into dough (this will make 2-9 inch crusts, you will use one for this recipe).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter (do not boil).
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: onion shortcake(a maxfield family recipe)
directions: Peel onion, slice, and saute slowly in butter.
Combine muffin mix, egg, milk, corn and tabasco.
Place in greased 8-inch square pan.
To onions, add sour cream, salt, dill and 1/2 cup cheese. Spread onion mixture over muffin mix.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: flavorful beef roast
directions: Place roast on large sheet of heavy duty foil in roaster pan. Spread steak sauce over roast.
Sprinkle with soup mix, salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup over top.
Fold foil to seal tightly. Bake in 325° oven for 3 1/2 hours.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Squish ingredients with hands.
Spray Pam on casserole dish and pour into dish.
Put several pads of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until bubbly and brown.

title: easy red jello salad
directions: Combine Jello with the boiling water, add the cold water. Cool slightly then add drained pineapple, orange segments, cranberries and nuts. Pour into 9 x 13 pan and refrigerate until set.

title: stovetop baked apples
directions: Wash and core apples, being careful not to cut through to bottom.
Peel a 1-inch strip from the top of each apple.
Mix honey, raisins and walnuts in a small bowl.
Fill apples with the honey mixture.
Place apples in a medium saucepan.
Add cinnamon stick and enough water to come up halfway up the apples.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Check for doneness.

title: russian cake
directions: Mix the sugar, egg and pineapple.
Let set until sugar dissolves (about 2 hours). Stir occasionally. Sift soda and salt with flour. Add nuts and mix with other ingredients.
Stir by hand 100 times. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs; mix flour, soda, baking powder and sift together.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Use iron skillet.
Combine oleo, sugar, egg yolks, salt and chopped dates in a skillet.
Cook very slowly and mash dates until all melts.
Turn off heat.
Add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies. Work all together and form little round balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in 3-quart pan.
Add milk gradually; mix thoroughly.
Bring to a bubbly boil on high heat, stirring continuously.
Reduce to medium heat and continue to boil without stirring until soft ball stage is reached.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Allow fudge to cool until 110° is reached.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Pour in lightly buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares. Makes about 3 dozen squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat well.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with bananas and cream. Fold in pecans.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans well.
Divide batter in pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: stuffed steak sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place steak flat on dressing block and cut steak in a manner to have a top "flap" and bottom "flap."
(For steaks with bones, leave bones in for cooking flavor/juices.) Place sliced onion, bell pepper and carrots on bottom flap of steak; sprinkle with Tabasco and preferred seasoning.
Close mix with top flap, securing with wooden toothpicks.
Apply flour to steak; put in broiler pan, cover with tinfoil (do not allow toothpicks to prick foil) and let bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours (regulate to avoid burning).

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and salt in heavy 3-quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat.
Fold in candies and cherries.
Spread immediately in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool. Cut in squares.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a baking dish, put broccoli.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Combine yolks, mustard and mayonnaise. Spoon into whites and top with paprika.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Pour in casserole and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with 1 package shredded cheese and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Can be cooked in crock-pot on high about 4 hours.
Add cheese about 15 minutes before serving.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Place meat in bottom of Dutch oven.
Do not brown.
Peel and chop carrots and potatoes into bite size pieces and place on top of meat with vegetables.
Mix soup and dry soup mix together. Spread on top.
Cover and cook for 6 hours at 250°.

title: chocolate cream truffles
directions: Melt over hot, not boiling, water the Nestle milk chocolate morsels.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream.
Add almond flavored liqueur; mix well.
Transfer to small bowl.
Chill until firm.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheets.
Shape into balls.
Roll in almonds until evenly coated.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen truffles.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl on low speed all ingredients, then rest!
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Soften Cheez Whiz in microwave. Saute onion in butter.
Add broccoli, rice, soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole with black-eyed peas
directions: Cook meat, onion flakes, garlic powder, tomatoes and black-eyed peas for about 15 minutes.
Add soups.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325° in a well-greased and floured tube pan.

title: layers
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: hernekeitto(pea soup)
directions: Soak the peas in water overnight.
In a large pot, bring the peas to a boil in the same water.
Skim.
Add the meat, carrots and onion and simmer about 2 hours or until the peas are tender. Remove the ham bone.
Take any meat off the bone and return to the soup.
Add the salt and pepper and serve.

title: bavarian cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Stir well with wooden spoon.
Chill at least one hour.
Serve.

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: In a heavy pot, make light brown roux using oil and flour. Add onion and shrimp; saute lightly.
Add garlic and stir.
Heat tomatoes.
Mash thoroughly; add to mixture.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Add parsley.
Add 1/3 cup chicken broth, if needed, to keep consistency of stew.
Add corn and cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add remaining broth.
Cook very slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.
If it is too thick, add water to desired consistency. Serves 8.

title: oven burritos
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain fat.
Add beans and taco sauce and let simmer.
Separate one can of rolls and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover pressed rolls with ground beef mixture and top with cheeses.
Top that with the other can of separated rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve with taco sauce, sour cream or any of your favorite toppings.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable to be dipped.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish. Drain pineapple and pour into casserole.
Add sugar and flour mixture on top, then grated Cheddar cheese.
Melt butter and crumble Ritz crackers onto top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good with chicken, turkey or ham.

title: "mawma" hall's yum yum cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and salt.
Stir.
Mix soda in milk and add to the shortening and sugar.
Add flour last. Use nuts or raisins if desired.
Serve warm with whipped cream. Bake at 325°.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let bread thaw, but don't let it rise.
Cook sausage; let cool and then add cheese and eggs.
Spread dough out about 9 x 13-inches and "mash" sausage mixture into dough.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with dry jello and fold thoroughly.
Let stand while pineapple and oranges drain, then fold them in and refrigerate.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.

title: country style steak(crock-pot style)
directions: Mix enough flour, salt and pepper to coat steak.
Roll steak in flour mixture.
Brown quickly in hot oil.
Place steaks in crock-pot.
Stir left over seasoned flour into hot grease.
Brown about a minute.
Then add soup, water and teaspoon of Kitchen Bouquet.
Heat until hot, bubbly and slightly thickened.
Pour over steaks and cook on low setting for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve over rice or creamed potatoes.

title: hush puppies #2
directions: Drop by
spoonfuls into deep hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add Bisquick or flour last. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake until golden brown on top, about 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cut into finger size squares. Makes about 40.

title: candied yams
directions: Cut up yams like thick french fries. Place in shallow baking dish.

title: scallops oriental(low cholesterol)
directions: Rinse scallops well and place in pan.
Combine next 4 ingredients and mix.
Brush scallops with the mixture.
Broil at 425° for 10 minutes or until slightly browned.
Turn scallops. Brush with remaining sauce.
Broil 10 minutes longer or until well browned.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Serves 6.

title: heavenly carrots
directions: Place carrots in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in croutons and cheese.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over carrot mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes or until browned.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lemon delight squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and pat into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; set aside.
Beat eggs well; stir in granulated sugar, lemon rind and juice.
Set aside. Mix together 1/4 cup flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°, until slightly golden.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Beat pudding and milk until stiff. Spread on top, making third layer and top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cover chicken with water in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil, reduce heat to low; cover and cook 30 minutes or until chicken is done. Remove chicken and cool.
Bone chicken and shred into large pieces.
Add to broth.
Stir in onion, corn, tomatoes, lima beans, garlic, bouillon cube, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Bring to boil, reduce heat to low, cover and cook 30 minutes.
Thicken with flour, if desired.

title: stuffed carrots
directions: Cut carrots 5 inches from top, reserving smaller end for another use.
Cook carrots, covered, in a small amount of water until tender-crisp; let cool.
Cut carrots in half lengthwise. Scoop out center of each.
Combine cracker crumbs and remaining ingredients; toss to mix.
Stuff carrots with mixture.
Place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until carrots are hot.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: old-timey yellow cake
directions: Beat eggs; add baking powder and pinch of salt.
Add melted butter or margarine and sugar.
Add sifted flour into mixture, adding milk alternately.
When well mixed, add vanilla and bake in 2 layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with boiled chocolate icing.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Let sit 20 minutes.
Add sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
When mixture boils, add butter and cook, stirring occasionally, until it reaches soft ball stage (236° to 238° on a candy thermometer).
It will
have turned a medium brown color.
Remove from heat and allow to cool to lukewarm (110°), then beat until mixture loses its gloss and starts to thicken.
Stir in nuts and turn into a buttered 8-inch square pan until firm.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 pounds.

title: glazed chocolate chip cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Add butter, vanilla, egg yolks and 1/2 cup milk and beat 2 minutes. Grate chocolate.
Add pecans and grated chocolate to batter.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Mix orange juice and powdered sugar.
Spoon mixture over top of warm cake.
Pierce surface of cake with fork to allow glaze to penetrate.
Freeze, if desired, after cake is cool.

title: microwave enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain fat.
Add dry mix and stir. Add chili, tomato sauce and water and stir.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread this mixture in round pizza pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice, strawberries and strawberry glaze.
Spread the "cheese" mixture on the crust.
(Crust should be cool.)
Spread the strawberries on top of the cheese mixture.
Store in the refrigerator until served.

title: steve's flank steak with herb stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound or score steak.
In skillet, heat butter.
Add onion and garlic; cook until brown.
Add mushrooms; cook 3 minutes.
Add nuts, parsley, bread cubes, seasonings, salt, pepper, egg and wine.
(Seasoned stuffing mix can be used instead of plain bread crumbs.)
Spread mixture on steak and roll lengthwise; tie with string at 2-inch intervals.
Brown meat on all sides in a little fat.
Add bouillon.
Cover and bake for 2 hours. To serve, cut into 1-inch slices and serve with pan drippings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute butter, onion and celery in large skillet.
Add chicken and mixture of 1 1/2 cups broth, 1 can tomato soup, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer while cooking spaghetti.
Mix spaghetti and sauce together.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: baked pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tenderloin on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Mix jam, salt, mustard and soy sauce in saucepan. Pour half over tenderloin, reserving the rest.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Heat remaining sauce in saucepan over low heat.
Slice tenderloin into 1/4-inch diagonal slices.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into a muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 8 biscuits.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Place prepared chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle olives over top.
Spread on Doritos and mash them down slightly to crush.
Add 3/4 of the cheeses.
In saucepan, bring to a boil: salsa, broth, soup and mushrooms.
Pour hot liquid over chicken mixture.
Add remaining cheeses over the top.
Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.
Serve with rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together in skillet; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into large casserole dish; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
I prefer to add the peas about 1/2 hour before it's finished baking.
This way they will keep their green color and better flavor.

title: grill cheese
directions: Get 2 pieces of bread and cheese.
Put it in the mikrowave on low for 3 minutes.
Take it out and eat it.

title: smoothies
directions: Blend in blender or processor until smooth.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs; beat after each egg. Add flour, lemon flavor, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: settlers beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp; crumble.
Add to browned hamburger meat and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes (or 3 to 4 hours in crock-pot).

title: johnny brazilia
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper together and drain off excess grease.
Combine all ingredients together, saving some cheese to put on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture very gradually.
Roll out on a pastry cloth and cut in desired shapes. Cookie press may be used.
Bake at 375° until light brown, about 8 minutes.
May be sprinkled with sugar prior to baking.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter. Add rest of ingredients, except sour cream, cheese and crab, until mixed. Slowly add sour cream. Stir constantly. Add can of crab and sharp Cheddar. Pour in casserole dish. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple cheese casserole(from sea captains in myrtle beach)
directions: Mix together. Mix Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat with electric mixer until smooth. Chill and serve with your choice of fruit.

title: heath brickle blonde brownies
directions: Cream together margarine and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in Bits 'O Brickle.
Spread evenly in well greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, if desired, frost with white or chocolate frosting.
It doesn't need it.
Makes 3 dozen brownies.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, place in refrigerator for a couple
hours.
Serve
with
celery,
cauliflower, carrots, radishes, cucumbers and broccoli.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Great for dip, glaze or dressing.

title: seafood stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut each eggplant into two equal parts.
Remove middle and chop.
Add onions, celery, margarine and garlic, smother until done.
Place buns and eggs into a bowl to soak.
When buns are completely soaked, mix well with chopped shrimp, smothered eggplant, crabmeat, parsley and green onions.
Season to taste. Boil shells of the eggplant for 10 minutes.
Stuff with mixture. Bake 15-20 minutes at 350°.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and remove skin.
Heat butter and oil in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 375° in the oven until butter is melted. Stir in remaining ingredients (except chicken).
Place chicken neatly sides down in pan turning to coat with herb mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake until thickest pieces are done, about 30 minutes.

title: honey herb marinade
directions: Combine all except the chicken breast in a zip top plastic bag.
Add chicken.
Seal bag turning to coat meat.
Refrigerate two hours or over night, turning the bag occasionally.
Grill as usual.
Makes about 1 cup (enough for 2 pounds meat).

title: casserole
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet.
Add sliced potatoes, shredded cabbage, salt & pepper and chopped onion.
Slice polish sausage or hot dogs on top of mixture.
Add garlic powder.
Cover top with American cheese.
Add 1 cup of water.
Cook until all is tender.

title: artichoke spears
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Bake in lightly greased Pyrex 10-inch pie plate at 352° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with small pieces of French bread or crackers and cut up apples and grapes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Mix gelatine and water.
Add to soup. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 5 to 6-cup mold and chill overnight.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in pumpkin.
Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs. Stir dry ingredients and mix with fruit.
Add pumpkin and fruit mixture to batter.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: pirogi(polish potato cheese dumplings)
directions: Boil potatoes, drain, add cheese and mash.
Mix in onions and pepper.
Set aside.

title: rice-stuffed ham rolls
directions: Combine rice and chicken.
Place 1/4 cup rice mixture in center of each ham slice.
Roll up and place seam side down in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon Mushroom-Cheese Sauce over ham rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until the sauce is bubbly.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook
potatoes	and
onion
with enough water to cover. Cook until tender.
Fry bacon or ham, cut in small pieces, and set aside.
Melt butter; add flour and milk and bring to boil. Add Velveeta
and
cook
until	melted.
Stir all ingredients together and salt and pepper to taste.

title: fried rice
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Add the Minute rice. Put lid on pan; remove from fire.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Add cherries to unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
In mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Increase oven temperature to 350°.
Add cheese mixture to cherries and bake for 30 minutes, or until cheese is baked.
Remove from oven; sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together thawed hash browns and 1/2 cup butter.
Add salt and pepper, undiluted cream of chicken soup, cheese, sour cream and onion.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together corn flakes and 1/2 cup butter; put on top of hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with all but 2 ounces (topping) of peanut butter chips over low heat until smooth.
Add marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour into a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle coconut over top.

title: barbecued mussels and clams with tomato-caper sauce
directions: Saute the onion in olive oil until soft but not browned.
Add the chopped tomatoes and cook for 2 minutes; add the capers, chopped herbs, wine and season to taste.
Set aside.
Broil the mussels and clams about 2 minutes or until the shells open. Discard one side of the shell.
Spoon on topping on each mussel and clam and heat for three minutes.
These can be served hot or cold.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift all dry ingredients together; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar together; add molasses and egg; mix thoroughly.
Add boiling water and vanilla to molasses mixture and blend well.
Slowly beat dry ingredients into molasses mixture; blend thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad(potluck)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well; add pineapple and refrigerate.
Serves up to 12.

title: microwave cake
directions: Stir well with a wooden spoon.
Place in a microwave Bundt cake pan.
Microwave on High for 13 minutes.
Take out; let cool. After cooling, mix a small amount of chocolate icing.
Place walnuts on top (optional).

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl; mix well.
Garnish with lemon or lime slices.

title: maudie's raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins, water and sugar for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix cornstarch in water.
Add vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at least 30 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel-nut corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Divide popcorn and nuts between 2 ungreased cookie sheets, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Cook brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until bubbly around edges.
Continue cooking 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda until foamy. Pour over popcorn and nuts.
Toss until well coated.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: easy beef(veal)
directions: Mix together.
Put in Dutch oven; bake for 4 to 5 hours at 325°, or place in crock-pot on low and cook until meat is tender.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all together. Dump into a greased casserole dish. Melt butter and mix in crackers. Put on top of pineapple mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes. I usually double this recipe.

title: mini meatball stew
directions: Combine meat, onion, chili powder and salt.
Shape into small balls.
Brown in a large skillet.
Drain fat.
Arrange vegetables in skillet with meatballs.
Pour on sauce.
Simmer 25 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix all together. Stir in 1 cup cranberries. Pour into greased 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake 60 to 75 minutes at 350° until done.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup and milk. In buttered casserole dish, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onions, soup mixture and cheese. Cover. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 15 minutes. Enjoy!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.
Makes a large batch.
You can use M&M's instead of chips.

title: potato bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, yeast and salt in bowl.
Add potato water, potatoes and oil to flour mixture.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Stir in enough more flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface; knead until smooth.
Place in oiled bowl; turn to oil top of dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double. Punch down and divide in half.
Shape into 2 loaves and place into 2 greased loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and pumpkin.
Add flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Place wax paper on a jelly roll pan.
Spray with Pam. Pour in batter and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove immediately from pan and place on towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top and roll in towel; cool.
Unroll and remove towel.
Spread with filling and roll again; serve.

title: very best chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix together until well blended.

title: cheese ball spread
directions: Allow cheese to become room temperature.
Beat cheeses, garlic powder and grated onion together in a mixer.
Put in refrigerator to get firm.
Divide mixture into 2 balls.
Place nut topping on Saran Wrap.
Roll mixture until well coated.
Store in refrigerator tightly wrapped.

title: hot salsa
directions: Mix everything together and let set overnight.

title: happy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: possum pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add baking powder and sugar, beating slowly until very stiff.
Fold in cracker crumbs and nuts. Mix well.
Bake in greased pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.

title: aunt alice's coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients; beat good.
Top with sugar and cinnamon.
Add nuts on top, if desired. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of the batter in a hot greased skillet. Add cheese, then remaining batter. Cook at 375° until done.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, then pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix well and sprinkle over the pie. Return to 400° oven for 10 minutes to brown.

title: crabbies
directions: Melt and mix cheese with butter.
Add rest of ingredients. Split muffins; spread mixture on muffins. Broil until lightly browned.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, onion, pepper, celery and pimiento.
Mix sugar and vinegar; bring to a rolling boil and pour over kraut, etc. Refrigerate.

title: veggie pizza
directions: God bless my little kitchen. I love its every nook.
Bless me as I do my work, wash my pots, pans and cook.

title: chocolate-peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter, gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg, beating well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies with a fork to 1/4-inch thickness in a crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chef salad a l'adam
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Add seasonings to taste. Let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Serve cold on a bed of fresh spinach leaves or leaf lettuce.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned and solid.

title: veggie pizza bars
directions: Use any combination of chopped, fresh vegetables in bite sizes: broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, onions, green pepper, radishes, etc.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, egg yolks, flour, milk, butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake about 25 minutes or until firm.
Beat egg whites and put on top.
Brown on top.
Makes 1 pie.

title: grandma imogene's refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, then add dry ingredients.
Add oats, nuts and chips; stir well.
Form into rolls and wrap in waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator or freeze until baking (if there is any dough left for baking).
Slice and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: rosemary silvay's ice cream kolacky(makes 12 dozen)
directions: Soften butter; cream together with softened ice cream.
Blend in flour a little at a time until it forms a soft dough.
Pinch off a small ball of dough, about the size of a quarter, and flatten center of ball with thumb.
Put spot of apricot, prune or other fruit filling in center of each kolacky.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wire rack and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: layered pea salad
directions: Layer raw vegetables, beginning with lettuce, in a deep glass bowl.
Drain peas and pour over top of vegetables.
Cover peas with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
