Seal with plastic wrap. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot or iced spiced tea
directions: Combine water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon in a large saucepan and bring to the boiling point.
Add tea bags and brew 4 minutes. Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks and add juices and rind.
Serve hot with a lemon slice.
Or chill and serve over ice with sliced lemon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crunchy brunch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Press the mixture firmly into a well-oiled jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool and cut into bars.

title: hamburger bake
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add hamburger and minced garlic.
Brown. Add tomato sauce and seasonings; simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook macaroni.
Alternate layers of meat sauce, macaroni and cheeses in a greased loaf pan, ending with meat sauce and Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until firm.
Serves 4.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Put lettuce, watercress, cucumber and oranges in bowl. Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and sesame seeds in a jar. Cove and shake well to mix. Toss with dressing just before serving.

title: sweet and sour beets
directions: Wash and trim beets.
Put in saucepan with 1-inch boiling water.
Add salt to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 25 to 45 minutes or until beets are tender.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup beet juice.
Peel and slice beets and set aside.

title: lucy's lemon squares
directions: Sift flour and sugar into bowl.
Blend in butter until well mixed.
Put evenly into bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mint candy
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Half dough and add your favorite mint flavoring.
Press into molds and/or roll and cut with cookie cutter.
Store in airtight container.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately. Add baking powder to last of flour.
Add flavoring.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Put into cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Do not open oven door until time is up.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Pour catsup in bowl.
Fill catsup bottle 3/4 full with water. Add Bulls Eye, Worcestershire sauce, chopped onion, brown sugar, mustard, lemon juice, Tabasco sauce, vinegar and teriyaki sauce. Cook 2 hours until thick.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook chicken.
Bone and cut into pieces.
Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Layer in buttered casserole with 1/3 can of noodles at a time, ending with the noodles.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until it bubbles all over.

title: cauliflower-broccoli toss
directions: Break cauliflower into bite-size pieces; wash thoroughly.
Set aside.
Trim broccoli, using only the flowerets; wash thoroughly.

title: spiced winter pears
directions: Boil vinegar, brown sugar, cloves and cinnamon.
Peel, cut into slices, core and add 8 pounds winter pears (Kieffer).
Boil them until they are tender.
Place them in jars; cover them with syrup and seal the jars.
If using Seckel pears, leave the stems on. Peel the pears and follow the recipe.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add the broth to the water while cooking.
Drain noodles.
Add the soup, chicken and cheese to hot noodles.
Add water, stir to mix.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
This is my family favorite.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sprinkle sugar over apples and let stand for 1 hour.
This is important.
Then stir in remaining ingredients.
One half of this can be made in 8 x 8-inch pan or entire recipe in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: browned rice
directions: Melt oleo in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; add onions and raw rice. Stir constantly over low heat until onion is cooked.
Pour in undiluted consomme.
Cover and bake at 375° for about 1 hour. (Spray casserole dish with Pam first and rice won't stick.)

title: punch bowl cake
directions: *I buy one already made in the bakery section.

title: chicken ortega
directions: Line greased 8 x 8 or 9 x 12-inch pan with diced chicken (pieces about 1-inch square).
Top with tortillas, chiles and sauce (made from soup, chicken broth and mushrooms mixed together).
Repeat layers. Sprinkle top with black olives and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Delicious!

title: stir-fried chicken and broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Slice broccoli thin, crosswise.
In large skillet on high heat, heat oil.
Sprinkle ginger and pepper over chicken and add to skillet; stir-fry for 3 minutes, or until brown.
Push chicken to side and add broccoli and onions.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.
In small bowl, mix 3/4 cup chicken broth, salt and sugar.
Pour into skillet and reduce heat to medium-high.
Cover and cook 2 minutes. Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water.
Stir until smooth. Stir into skillet and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with croutons.

title: boiled 7 minute frosting
directions: Combine ingredients in double boiler with water boiling.
Beat 7 minutes with mixer until stiff peaks.
Add vanilla and blend.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread according to box.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish and pour 1/2 cornbread mixture in it.
Place ground meat next and then a layer of onions, followed by a layer of cheese.
Spread creamed corn, then jalapeno pepper and then another layer of cheese.
Pour on another layer of cornbread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Combine in pan the pineapple and juice, cornstarch, pie filling, sugar and food coloring.
Cook over low heat until thickened; remove from heat.
Add dry jello.
Cool.
Stir in nuts and bananas.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped topping.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork slowly in hot shortening.
Add 1 cup water with bouillon cube and 1 teaspoon salt (dissolve cube in water with salt).
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Blend the two mixtures.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut, then roll in mixture of 2 Tbsp. sugar and 2 tsp. cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes (I bake mine 8 minutes**).
These cookies will puff up at first, then flatten with crinkled tops. Yields about 36 cookies.
(I double the recipe.)

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze dry.
Stir in soup mix, sour cream and mayo.
Stir in spinach.
Cover; chill for 2 hours.
Hollow out rye bread.
Fill with dip and serve with little pieces of rye bread.

title: lemon-strawberry punch
directions: Combine the frozen lemonade and orange juice concentrates and the strawberries that have been half-thawed with their juice. Place in punch bowl with ice.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining flour until dough is stiff. Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover with a cloth and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: corn bread casserole(servings 4-6)
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 11x7x2 inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 400 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until top and edges are golden brown.

title: cheesy onion dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Combine cheese with all other ingredients after softened.
Mix well.
Chill.
Makes about 1 pint.

title: swedish apple pie(from helyette lachance)
directions: You will need 10-inch pie plate.

title: baked fish
directions: Put fish in shallow pan.
Pour on soup.
Mix oleo and crumbs. Sprinkle on fish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika or parsley.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: seven seas sauteed mushrooms(serves 6)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a frying pan.
Add mushrooms. Pour in wine and dressing.
Saute on medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks to spear.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together melted margarine and crumbs and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix margarine, eggs and sugar.
Beat 15 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour over crust.
Layer sliced bananas over filling.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple layer and top with cherries and nuts.
Chill at least 12 hours before serving.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat the oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups or grease bottoms only.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, lemon peel and salt; mix well.
Stir in the berries.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut off tops of tomatoes.
Carefully scoop out insides with a spoon and save.
Saute onion and zucchini in 1/4 cup butter.
Add tomato (mashed) that was saved.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Continue to cook until cheese melts.
Spread 1/2 cheese mixture on bottom of 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Arrange potatoes and onions over cheese mixture. Top with remainder of cheese mixture.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add sugar and milk. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Serve with Cool Whip on top of pie.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Transfer to baking dish.
Pour rice over pork chops.
Mix together tomato sauce, taco seasoning and water. Pour over rice and pork chops.
Slice bell pepper into rings and place on top of pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Top with American cheese slices. Allow cheese to melt before serving.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Chill and serve.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: If you make a lot, add more soup.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook pepper, onion and celery in butter on low until tender. Add hamburger, salt, pepper, garlic salt and mustard.
Cook until hamburger is done.
Add tomato soup, water and tomato sauce with sugar to taste.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Serve over cooked noodles. Serves 3 or 4.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Combine butter, sugar, flour and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add peaches.
Do not stir. Bake at 350°
until golden brown (about 45 minutes).
Yields about 8 servings.

title: chicken divine
directions: Mix soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
In baking dish, put broccoli, then chicken.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Spread cheese on top of mixture.
Put bread crumbs that have been mixed with butter over cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pink salad
directions: Stir lemon juice into milk and add all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix together and put in baked or graham cracker pie shell. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: doughnuts, raised
directions: Scald milk, stir in sugar, salt and oleo.
Cover.
Put warm water in bowl and sprinkle yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add warm milk mixture, egg and half flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead.
Let rise until doubled.
Roll out and cut; rise about 1 hour more and fry.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until peanuts pop and turn to honey color.
Add soda, stirring fast, then pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: italian chocolate mozettes
directions: Mix all together.
Divide mixture in two and form into 2 rolls, each the length of a cookie sheet.
Place the rolls on the sheet and bake until tester is dry.
Immediately spread with vanilla icing in the can and sprinkle with nonpareils.
Cut on the slant and leave until they are cold.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place corn in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt oleo.
Add onion and green pepper and cook; add to corn.
Combine eggs, Jiffy cornbread mix, 1 cup of the Cheddar cheese and the sour cream. Combine all together.
Sprinkle 1 cup Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack pickles in jars and add 3 teaspoons dill seed, 1/4 teaspoon alum and 1 clove of garlic.
Combine water, vinegar and salt and heat until boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over pickles and seal.

title: slick cabbage casserole
directions: Place a layer of chopped cabbage in the bottom of a casserole dish.

Then add diced potatoes, chopped onions, green beans, mushrooms, hamburger or bulk sausage (uncooked), tomato sauce and Parmesan cheese or other shaker-type cheese in successive layers. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on back of cake box, omitting water.
Mix in soup, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix cottage cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese and sauce.
Make layers in this order: noodles, sauce, 1/3 noodles, cottage cheese mix (1/2), Swiss cheese, sauce (1/3), noodles, cottage cheese mix, noodles, sauce (1/3) and Mozzarella cheese.

title: citrus sunshine punch
directions: Combine juices and water; chill.
Just prior to serving, add 2 quarts cold ginger ale.
Pour over ice cubes or ice ring and serve.
Makes 60 cups.

title: chicken salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, sour cream and seasonings.
Toss with first 5 ingredients.
Chill and serve on crisp lettuce.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix with fork.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.
Serve with any fresh vegetables, snack crackers or chips.

title: meringue for pies
directions: Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat at high speed until peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating continuously.
When stiff peaks form, add vanilla.
Spread over pies or banana pudding and bake at 425° until brown (approximately 5 to 6 minutes).

title: new year's day bean soup
directions: Wash beans and place in a large kettle.
Cover with water; add salt.
Soak overnight.

title: black-eyed pea soup(makes 12 to 16 servings)
directions: *Fresh black-eyed peas are often available in supermarkets in the produce section.
If desired, substitute 1 pound dried black-eyed peas, cooked, for the fresh.

title: mom's dill pickles
directions: Boil together first 3 ingredients.
Wash and pack pickles in quart jars.
Put in alum the size of 2 peas, 3 or 4 pieces of garlic, dill to taste and 3 red hot candies in each jar.
You may also add 2 red hot peppers or crushed red peppers.
This will cover 6 quarts.
After the water boils, let it set about 5 minutes, then pour over the pickles in jars and seal.
Boil your lids also.
Sometimes the jars don't seal, but they don't spoil. Ready to eat in about 3 weeks.

title: hidden valley oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil with dry ingredients.
Heat and mix well.
Pour over oyster crackers.
Toss with spatula every hour or so.

title: suzie's rolls
directions: Scald milk, add margarine, sugar and salt.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add yeast to milk mixture.
Then add milk mixture to beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, knead.
Place in greased bowl, or spray with cooking spray, cover with wax paper and then tea towel.
Let rise in warm place 3-4 hours.
Roll on floured surface. Divide into 3 equal sections.
Roll each section out to a round 1/8-inch thick.
Spread with soft margarine.
Cut with a pizza cutter into 8 triangle pieces.
Roll each up going from wide end to sharp point.
Place on greased cookie sheet, shaping each one into a crescent.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake 400 F 8-12 minutes.
Freezes beautifully.

title: jail house rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water and set aside.
Mix potatoes and oleo while potatoes are hot.
Add eggs, salt and sugar.
Blend very well. Blend in flour and yeast water.
Mix well.
Place dough in a large bowl.
Cover with a wet towel and refrigerate until ready to be used.
Roll out thin.
Cut, brush with melted butter and place in a greased pan.
Let rise about 2 to 3 hours.
Bake in 450° oven about 10 to 20 minutes.
This dough will keep in the refrigerator for about a week (keep towel wet).
These are better if you use a bean can for a cutter.
Cut and butter tops and then fold half over and let rise.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Butter a square pan.
Place the apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown. Serves 6

title: creamy salsa dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Chill for at least an hour. Serve with chips.
Something a little different for salsa.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Mold into a ball and roll in crackers.

title: no-peek oven stew
directions: Put everything in a roasting pan.
Cut 1 1/2 pounds stewing beef in cubes.
Bake at 275° for 3 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cool orange spritzer
directions: Place 1 orange slice in each of 8 glasses.
Combine club soda and orange juice; mix well.
Pour over orange slice and serve. For added coolness, use crushed ice.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix the cheese and cream together with a wooden spoon, then beat vigorously.
Stir in the Worcestershire sauce and seasoning to taste.
Spoon into a serving bowl and chill before serving.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: fruit cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add rest of ingredients and mix well with mixer. Refrigerate overnight. Divide into 3 balls. Roll in chopped nuts. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: baby lima bean and sausage casserole
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Put in clean water; boil 5 minutes with 1 tablespoon baking soda.
(Watch - don't boil over.) Drain.
Rinse in clear water; drain.
Place in large casserole. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Stir 3 times while baking.

title: fish supreme
directions: Thaw fish enough to separate.
Arrange in a buttered Pyrex baking dish, sprinkle fish with pepper and dot with the butter. Mix the shrimp in the cheese sauce.
Spread over fish; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes in a preheated oven.
Serve with lemon wedges and parsley sprigs. Makes 4 servings.

title: easy jam tarts
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and the milk until fluffy.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl cut margarine into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in half the cream cheese mixture until well combined.
Shape into ball in bowl.

title: lentil soup
directions: Put together in a pressure cooker; cook 15 minutes.
Serve with fat-free crackers.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cook
broccoli	according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly.
Saute	onion in butter until tender.
Stir onions into broccoli.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and pour into 10-inch buttered pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in water until done.
Cool.
Remove from bones and return meat to broth.
Reheat to boiling.
Mix margarine, salt, pepper and baking powder in mixing bowl.
Add hot water.
Stir until margarine is melted and other ingredients dissolve.
Add flour until dough is stiff.
Roll out thin on floured board.
Cut into strips and add to boiling chicken broth.
After dumplings cook, add milk.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, refrigerate and congeal slightly.

title: roast in gravy(no salt)
directions: Brown
roast
in
large skillet.
Be sure to mix mayonnaise with
soup,
then add water to soup mixture.
Mix well. Pepper roast
and	put
chopped
onion and pepper over roast. Then
pour soup mixture over roast.
Cook over low heat until tender and gravy is thick.
Add more water, if needed.

title: sour cream lemon pie(makes one 9-inch baked pie shell)
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch together.
In a medium saucepan, add sugar and cornstarch mixture.
Add beaten eggs and slowly add lemon juice until blended.
Add lemon rind.
Add milk; blend. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened like a thick pudding.
Be careful and don't scorch bottom.

title: black-eyed gumbo
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Cover with water and boil with salt pork for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: blue ribbon swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and mustard and sprinkle over steak; pound in meat.
In heavy skillet, brown in oil.
Add water and Worcestershire sauce and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours in covered skillet.
Pour mushroom soup over meat and cook 10 minutes longer. Serves 6 to 8.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Add apples and celery; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill. Just before serving, sprinkle with walnuts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Freeze.
Before serving, place on cookie sheet still frozen.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 60 balls.

title: tang pie
directions: Combine sour cream, sweetened condensed milk and Tang powder in a bowl.
Mix well.
Put into pie shell.
Spread with whipped topping and garnish.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer for two minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch round pans, according to package directions.

title: baked taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add the packet of taco seasoning and mix well.
Pour in the chili tomatoes and stir together.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/2 of the hamburger/tomato mixture, 1/2 bag of the Fritos, 1/2 of the Velveeta cheese slices, 1/2 of the shredded cheese.
Now put another layer of remaining hamburger/tomato mixture and the rest of the cheese.
(Reserve the 1/2 bag of Fritos for after casserole is baked.)
Bake for about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and put the remaining Fritos on casserole.
Serve hot.

title: tomato relish salsa
directions: Pour salt on tomatoes, onions, green pepper and celery. Refrigerate overnight.
Drain but don't press.
Put in large kettle and add pepper, sugars and vinegar.
Cook until thick. Boil and stir another 35-40 minutes.
Don't let it stick to pan. Put in hot jars and seal.
Great with chips and meats as a relish. For a milder salsa taste, decrease black pepper usage.

title: crab or shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup.
Add dissolved gelatin (do not add gelatin until soup is heated).
Cool slightly.
Add other ingredients and put in mold; chill overnight.
Unmold 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature; mix together.
Optional is coarsely ground black pepper on top.
Food processor works well. May be frozen.
When thawed, put in processor again to restore creamy texture.

title: just right chocolate chip cookies
directions: With mixer, beat shortenings together until fluffy.
Add both sugars; beat until well blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, mix together flour, soda, salt and pudding mix.
Gradually add to beaten mixture, stirring well. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 18 minutes. (Longer baking time yields a crunchier cookie; less time a chewy one.)
Yield:
4 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli ham ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop ham, broccoli and onion. Finely snip parsley.
Grate Swiss cheese.
Mix all ingredients together except rolls and set aside.
Arrange crescent triangles in a circle on a round baking pan or pizza stone with bases overlapping in center and points to the outside.
There should be a 3-inch diameter circle in center.
Evenly spoon filling over crescent rolls.
Fold points of triangles over filling and tuck under base at center.
Filling will not be completely covered. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bahama chicken
directions: Wash chicken and place on broiler pan that has been sprayed with Pam cooking spray. Bake in
a 400° oven for about 40 minutes. While chicken is baking, mix together the other 5 ingredients. Brush on chicken and broil 2 to 3 minutes on each side.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Place 1/2 of the cookie crumbs in the bottom of the cake pan.
Press firmly.
Beat milk, vanilla, sugar and cream cheese in a bowl until creamy.
Add dry pudding mix and mix well.
Pour mixture over cookies in pan.
Add other layer of cookie crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with sprinkles of crumbs.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sunshine sauce
directions: Beat egg yolk with sugar and whip cream until light; combine with sugar mixture.
Beat egg white.
Add vanilla and fold into cream mixture.
Delicious with sponge cake.

title: dr. jonas' bran muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, add mixed dry ingredients.
Add cereal.
Mix altogether and place in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Batter stores in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Excellent fiber food source.
Eat one muffin daily.

title: maid service pancakes
directions: Beat eggs. Add buttermilk, salad oil, cream and yeast. Stir, then add flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt, which has been sifted all together. Stir thoroughly. Set in refrigerator overnight. Bake on hot griddle.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix boiling water, Jell-O, pineapple with juice and blueberry pie filling. Pour in a large dish and let congeal. Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Add pecans. Spread over congealed Jell-O.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Cream butter well and blend in sugars.
Beat eggs and add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in coconut, oatmeal and Rice Krispies. Drop by spoonful onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: all-bran rolls
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Mix hot water and all-bran.
Let cool.
After it has cooled, add eggs and salt.
Dissolve yeast cakes in warm water and add to mixture, then add flour.
Make into rolls.
Let rise 2 hours or until light.
These need to rise only once and may be kept in refrigerator or may be frozen before rising.

title: snickers bar salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients; fold in the apples. Refrigerate before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the brown sugar, cornstarch and egg yolks well, then add milk.
Cook until thick.
Add 3 teaspoons vanilla.
Add peanut butter.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue or Cool Whip.
Makes 2 big pies.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine together and bring to a boil.
Let boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly and quickly drop on waxed paper. (This mixture cools very fast so work quickly).

title: old-fashioned bread dressing
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet. Add celery and onion. Saut until tender. Stir in thyme, sage, salt (if using) and pepper. Set aside. Mix dried broken bread and parsley into the vegetable mixture. In medium saucepan, heat broth to a simmer. Place dressing mixture in a large mixing bowl. Starting with about 2 cups of hot broth, pour over top of bread mixture, stirring until evenly moistened, adding more broth for a moist consistency. Transfer mixture to a shallow casserole. Cover and bake in a preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes. Uncover and continue to bake until lightly browned, about another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: texas taco dip
directions: Spread beans on pizza pan; mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning together and spread over beans on pan.
Top with chopped green onions, then olives, then cheese.
Spread on crackers or use chips.

title: pizza supper pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain and spoon into pie shell.
Combine eggs, milk, cheese and seasonings.
Mix and pour on meat.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Spread pizza sauce over pie and top with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes longer.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: good ole turkey sandwich
directions: Don't know what to do with the leftover Thanksgiving turkey?

title: garden zucchini pie
directions: Combine 1 egg, onion, Parmesan cheese and potatoes.
Mix well. Transfer to 9-inch pie plate or 10-inch quiche dish.
Pat in bottom and up sides.
Bake, uncovered, at 400°
for 35 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: party pizza
directions: Brown pork sausage in a skillet and drain.
Stir in Velveeta cheese (cut into thin slices or chunks).
Add only about 1/8 cup ketchup and 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce.

title: vanilla delight
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1/2 wafers in pan.
Melt chocolate and margarine.
Remove from heat and add 10x sugar, salt, vanilla and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Chop peanuts and spread over chocolate mixture.
Cut ice cream into 5 slices lengthwise.
Put over chocolate mixture.
Put other half of wafers over ice cream.
Top with whipped topping.
Freeze.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cheese with a fork until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup nuts, pepper, pineapple, onion, and salt.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Chill 5 hours or overnight.

title: pork chops florentine
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart oblong baking dish.
Brown pork chops in lard or drippings seasoned with pepper.
Cook spinach according to package directions, but reduce cooking time to 5 minutes.
Drain spinach.
Fold in soup and pour into baking dish.

title: spinach, lettuce and bacon salad(tired of plain lettuce salad?  try this spinach salad recipe.)
directions: Tear spinach and lettuce into bite sized pieces into a large bowl.
In a skillet, fry the bacon until crisp, then drain the fat.
Combine with spinach and lettuce.
Chop eggs and add to mixture.
Pour in dressing and toss lightly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread; cool and cut into cubes.
Mix together and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Fry hamburger, onions and peppers together until brown.
Drain hamburger.
Add tomato sauce and simmer.
Into large baking dish, add a layer of macaroni, then strips of American cheese, then sauce.
Repeat.
Top with layer of cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes, or cook in microwave for 5 minutes.

title: parmesan fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fish in a shallow baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick spray.
Spread mixture evenly over fillets.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil until light colored.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Fold in apples and chopped nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cottage cheese dumplings(topfenknodel)
directions: Pour light cream over diced white bread.
Allow to soak in. Stir until smooth.
Beat together butter and egg yolks until foamy. Add cottage cheese and salt.
Fold in white bread soaked in cream.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, peanuts, and syrup in skillet and cook until tan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter and baking soda.
Pour on buttered foil.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: new england clam chowder(4 servings)
directions: Saute onion in salt pork until onions are clear. Crush crackers and stir into onion mixture.
Stir in clam juice, potato, bay leaf and black pepper.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add milk and clams. Heat to under simmering point.
Do not simmer because it will toughen the clams.

title: lemon congealed salad
directions: Mix jello, water and sugar.
Let it start to congeal.
Fold in the last 6 ingredients to the lemon jello.
Refrigerate.

title: 6-week muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then add eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Mix well in large container.
Store in covered container in refrigerator and use as desired.
Grease muffin tins; fill 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: stewed tomato casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Stir cubed bread into butter.
Stir until bread cubes become slightly brown and toasted.
Set aside.
Mix soup, water, stewed tomatoes, brown sugar and salt in bowl.
Add toasted bread cubes; mix well.
Put into a 2-quart buttered casserole dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Stir in melted butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour and salt; stir into mixture. Fold in nuts.
Pour into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (or less).
Cool and frost.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces.
Mix pudding with milk. Gently mix ice cream, pudding and cake.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan and ice with Cool Whip.
Crumble Heath bar over top (optional). Freeze.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook the broccoli and drain.
Arrange in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break up chicken and arrange on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo and lemon juice and pour over chicken layer.
Sprinkle bread crumbs next, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a long Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Beat eggs
with
cup
of
the
butter,
the melted chocolate and
the sugar for 5 minutes until smooth and thick. In a
separate bowl, beat peanut butter with the remaining 1/4 cup of butter.
While
beating, add up to 1/3 cup of the cream to make the
peanut butter a spreadable consistency that will swirl readily
into
the	chocolate mixture.
Spoon chocolate mixture into
pie
shell.
Swirl
peanut butter into chocolate mixture. Beat
remaining
cream adding small amount of sugar. Top pie with cream and garnish with chocolate shavings.

title: banana custard pie
directions: Prebake tart shell in advance.
In a large saucepan, put sugar, flour and salt.
Mix well, then add eggs.
Mix then add milk.
Cook until mixture thickens, then add vanilla, butter and banana slices and pour in tart shell.
Add meringue.
Bake until lightly brown.

title: diet brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan; set aside. Place egg whites in large bowl.
Beat with spoon until slightly foamy.
Add oil and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Stir in sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Pour into pan and bake at 330° for 22 to 26 minutes; avoid overbaking.
Cool completely before cutting.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain well.
Combine eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Beat with mixer.
Pour croutons in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sausage and mushrooms.
Carefully pour egg mix over top of these layers.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: wester apple pie(don't like cinnamon?  this is for you.)
directions: Mix apple slices with sugar and flour.
Sprinkle lemon extract over fruit and mix lightly with a fork to distribute it evenly. Put apples in pie shell; dot with butter and put on top crust. Sprinkle crust with white sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat and bake at 350° until apples are done.

title: chili sauce
directions: Simmer 2 hours. Add 1 quart vinegar and cook until mixture thickens slightly.
Can in jars.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and thinly slice solid green tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Flour each side.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Put 1 layer of tomatoes in pan; brown on both sides.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towel or brown paper bag.
Keep warm while cooking remainder of tomatoes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Fry garlic and onion until soft.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir twice. This can also be cooked in a bean pot or a crock-pot.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in water until tender and drain thoroughly. Stir in butter. Mix mustard and salt with 1 tablespoon hot water and add to half and half. Add beaten egg. Mix in cheese, leaving enough to sprinkle on top. Pour into a buttered casserole and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard is set and top is crusty.

title: slaw for deep freezer
directions: Place cabbage in salt water (1 teaspoon salt) and soak for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk salad(also makes a delightful parfait dessert)
directions: Mix undrained pineapple and gelatin; bring to a boil.
Cool this mixture; add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
This may be poured into a flat dish or into individual molds or parfait glasses and garnished on top.
Freezes well or keeps in refrigerator for several days.

title: icebox cake
directions: Prepare jello; refrigerate.
Place can of milk in top freezer until slushy.
Mix jello, milk and sugar together.
Beat until well mixed.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, place vanilla wafers on bottom. Cover with jello-milk mixture.
Place pineapple over that.
Repeat steps until layers are desired height.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice in a 2-quart bowl.
Mix all ingredients, except potatoes.
When mixed well, add diced potatoes to mixture.
Stir to coat potatoes.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: pistachio congealed salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Place into a serving bowl.
Makes 10 (1 cup) servings.

title: rice square chews
directions: Mix syrup (or honey) and sugar in top of double boiler.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Add peanut butter and stir until well blended.
Add rice squares, stirring enough to coat rice.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: quick casserole
directions: Wash potatoes well.
Slice thin with peel left on.
Slice onion thin.
Place in a microwave dish, covered.
Cook 6 minutes on High.
Let casserole set 2 minutes.
Use more potatoes and onions for a larger dish.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix, stir and pour over the top of salad.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and put in ovenproof dish; top with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy meat sandwiches
directions: First mix water, mustard and ketchup in a bowl.
Place meat in a pan with the mustard, water and ketchup.
Let meat, mustard, water and ketchup simmer until the meat is hot.
Put some meat on a bun or eat the meat alone.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix with blender.
Makes lots.
Freeze the leftovers until next time.
Spread on crackers (taste just like Winschullers cheese spread).

title: squash rolls
directions: Put squash, milk, sugar, salt and margarine in bowl and cool. When lukewarm, add yeast dissolved in water.
Add half of the flour.
Beat well.
Gradually work in the rest of the flour.
Turn onto a floured board and knead about 5 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Shape into rolls.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and allow to rise again.
Bake at 375° about 20 or 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir in each of ingredients in order given before adding the next.
Batter is thick.
They are done when the tops crack.
Bake at 375°.

title: stay up all night cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites; add vanilla and then gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Add chocolate chips and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put in oven and turn off heat. Leave all night.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to mixture.
Add pecans. Bake 350, about 10 minutes, less if you want them chewy.

title: florida pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients and add 1/3 cup lemon juice.
Pour into 2
deep dish graham pie shells and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, with skin, until done.
Cool, then cube the potatoes.
Crumble bread.
Cube cheese.
Add all ingredients together into a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll out like a rope.
Cut into pieces approximately 3-inches.
Roll in sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frozen punch base
directions: Mix together the gelatin, sugar and boiling water until sugar and gelatin are dissolved.
Add the frozen lemonade drink mix and the pineapple juice.
Stir well and freeze.

title: best lemonade
directions: In 1-quart jar with tight fitting lid, shake sugar, lemon peel and hot water until sugar is dissolved.
Add lemon juice. Refrigerate.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix together next six ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Add any vegetables you like:
dill pickle slices, snow peas, etc.

title: panama sal
directions: Blend melted margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Put into greased 13 x 9-inch pan; blend cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar (all except 1/4 cup of powdered sugar).
Pour over first layer and bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining powdered sugar over warm cake and cut into 1-inch squares while still warm.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Slice French bread lengthwise in half.
Take a spoon and take bread out of center until about 2 inches.
Set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in large bowl, stirring well after each addition.
In separate bowl, stir together the dry ingredients, except walnuts, and add all at once to zucchini mixture.
Stir well.
Add walnuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 75 to 90 minutes. Flip out of pans immediately; cool on wire racks.
You should cool completely before slicing, but I always have to have a slice warm with butter!

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat the pineapple juice and add the Jell-O.
Mix well and cool. Add the buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.
Add the pineapple.
When mixture begins to congeal, put into mold.

title: okra goulash
directions: Wash and snip ends off of okra.
Add 1 pint boiling water. Add all other ingredients and boil on medium heat for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: Layer chicken, celery, onions, almonds and eggs. Mix mayo, soup and seasonings. Grease casserole pan. Put layers in; pour soup mixture in. Cover with chips. Bake at 350° until bubbling and browned.

title: lime and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve 2 packages of Jell-O in 1 cup water.
Let congeal; then whip in ice cream and pineapple.
Let congeal.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 40 minutes in 300° oven.
Cut into squares and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: basic sweet rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water and set until doubled.
Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool.
Add yeast mixture and eggs. Blend; add flour, stirring while adding until light and smooth. Dough should be light and smooth, almost sticky.
Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth.
Put into buttered bowl and let rise to double.
Punch down; let rise again.
Shape into desired forms such as cloverleaf, Parker House or crescent rolls or roll out and fill with your favorite filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange almond salad
directions: Chop lettuces and slice or chop onion.
Toss together with oranges and almonds.

title: jennine's spicy enchiladas
directions: Cook the meat in a large, flat pan; drain the grease.
Add your grated jalapenos, onion, garlic salt, spicy beans and black pepper.
Let simmer for 1 minute, then remove from heat.
Heat enchilada sauce.
In a flat, round pan, heat Crisco oil. Dip tortillas until soft.
Dab with paper towel to remove grease. Roll 1 tortilla, filled with meat mixture, and place a toothpick in the center to keep from falling apart.
Finish with the rest of the meat mixture and tortillas by doing the same thing, placing them into a Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Pour half of heated enchilada sauce on top, making sure to get the edges well. Sprinkle your cheese on top and place in the oven for 5 minutes. Remove from the oven and add your tomatoes.
Serve with white rice and black beans.

title: party continental chicken
directions: Cover bottom of flat, greased baking dish with chipped beef. Wrap each piece of chicken with a piece of bacon; place on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over all.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Serve over hot, buttered noodles or with long grain rice.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef in pan with onions.
Add salt, pepper, catsup and tomato sauce.
Put in casserole dish and cover with cheese. Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° until biscuits brown, about 20 minutes.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce and mix.
Add cold water, then rest of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: swiss steak
directions: Wipe steak with damp cloth.
Cut into serving portions.
Mix flour and seasonings.
Pound flour mixture into steak with meat pounder.
Heat shortening in frying pan.
Add onion and cook until golden, stirring two or three times.
Remove onion and set aside. Add steak and cook until golden brown, turning once.
Return onion to pan.
Pour tomatoes over steak.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add the eggs, syrup, oats and coconut.
Mix well and put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
(Tastes like a pecan pie.) Yields 1 pie.

title: minetre's miracle
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat egg yolks until light; beat into creamed mixture.
Soak macaroons in bourbon.
Beat chocolate into creamed mixture; add vanilla and pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into chocolate mixture. Line bottom and sides of 10 inch spring-form pan with split lady fingers.
Alternate layers of soaked macaroons with chocolate mixture in lined pan.
Decorate top with whipped cream. Refrigerate.
Makes 16-20 servings.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Wash chicken and pat dry with a paper towel. Heat margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper according to taste. Coat chicken with mixture. Place in pan. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes. Turn chicken and bake about 30 minutes or until the thickest pieces of chicken are done.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Stir all together and grease batter with Wesson oil (I grease bowls).
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Knead on floured board and shape.
Let rise 1 hour and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: champagne punch
directions: Defrost High's frozen fruit punch for at least 1 hour in punch bowl.
Add sherbet.
Pour champagne and ginger ale into mixture. Sherbet will slowly melt.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: italian ground beef and mac
directions: Cook beef, onion, green pepper and celery in a large frypan until beef is lightly browned and onion is clear.
Drain.
Break up large pieces of tomatoes.
Add tomatoes, tomato puree and seasonings to beef mixture.
Simmer 15 minutes to blend flavors. Stir in cooked macaroni.
Heat to serving temperature.
Yields four 1 1/3 cup servings.
Contains 330 calories per serving.

title: stew-betty
directions: Cook 5 hours, covered, at 250°.

title: cooked vidalia onions
directions: Cook in a covered pan.
Season with salt, pepper and margarine or fat back grease.

title: holly treats
directions: Heat butter, marshmallows and vanilla; add green food coloring, then stir in cornflakes.
Drop by teaspoons and flatten with fork; add cinnamon candies and multi-colored sprinkles before they cool.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Line muffin tin with cupcake papers.
Place a vanilla wafer in each cup.
Fill half full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: about 24.

title: easy pasta
directions: Cook shells as directed on package.
Drain water; do not rinse.
Fold in Mozzarella cheese and mix well.
Pour in the Ragu, more or less depending on individual taste.

title: 2 fruit pie
directions: In graham crust, put blueberry pie filling on bottom.
In another bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together until smooth.
Place on top of blueberry filling, then top with second pie filling.
Chill for about an hour.

title: date nut crispies
directions: Cook the margarine, sugar and dates over low heat for 10 minutes, beating frequently.
Cool slightly. Add Rice Krispies and chopped pecans. Form small balls. Roll in coconut or powdered sugar. Chill. Store in airtight container.

title: chicken noodle soup(no fat)
directions: In a large pan, boil chicken in about 3 quarts of water; when chicken breast and set aside.
(I remove all skin before boiling.) In water, add
all other ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Add noodles; cook until tender or add 3 cups of rice for chicken and rice variation.

title: hot fudge sheet cake
directions: Stir together in mixing bowl flour and sugar.
Bring to a boil in saucepan oleo, cocoa and water.
Pour this mixture over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, slightly beaten eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat well (hand beat; do not use mixer).
Pour into greased 16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: In a round 1-inch pan or glass pie dish, press crescent rolls to bottom, to form a crust.
In a 350° oven, bake crust until lightly golden.
Shred or chop all veggies; place 10 mushrooms on side for garnish.
Place veggies on the side.
Mix and cream the cream cheese, dill weed, garlic powder and 2/3 cup mayonnaise. Mix to a smooth texture.
Spread mixture on cooled crust and top with shredded vegetables, one layer at a time, to fill pan or pie plate.
Garnish around outer edge with mushroom slices. Refrigerate and slice when ready for use.
Great appetizer or finger food.

title: curried fruit casserole
directions: Put fruit in 1 - 1/2 quart casserole. Cook the remaining ingredients slowly until thick. Pour over fruit and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pea casserole
directions: Saut green peas in butter or oleo. Add sauteed vegetables. Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: hannah's apple cake
directions: Combine apples, banana and sugar; mix and place in covered bowl or Ziploc bag overnight or up to 4 days, the longer, the better.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, 3/4 cup coconut and 1 cup of walnuts; set aside. Beat eggs and oil together.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and mix with flour mixture.
Add apples; mix well and pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° preheated oven.

title: chocolate cherry nut banana bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add the next seven ingredients, mix well. Fold in cherries and chocolate chips.

title: hot rolls
directions: Cool the milk to lukewarm and mix thoroughly with sugar, shortening and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and add to the mixture.
Add egg and flour; mix with a spoon.
Cover and let rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, then knead the dough on a floured surface until smooth.
Roll 1/4 inch thick and cut.
Brush with butter and as for Parker House rolls place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 3/4 hour.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit soup
directions: Add together, mix and refrigerate.

title: lemon orange carrots
directions: In medium saucepan, combine carrots, marmalade, ReaLemon and margarine.
Stir to coat evenly.
Heat through.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange
chicken
in
a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup with wine or water and stir well.
Spoon sauce evenly over chicken, then sprinkle with
stuffing
mix.
Drizzle
melted
butter
over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip caramel cake
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk, stirring constantly.
Mix cake mix with butter and 1/3 cup milk.
Mix well.
Press 1/2 of mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pour melted caramels over chips.
Sprinkle remainder of cake mixture over top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.

title: dip
directions: Mix together.
Let stand for about 1 hour before serving.

title: pecan pie cookies
directions: To

make cookies, stir butter and sugar on low speed in large bowl of electric mixer. Add corn syrup and egg yolks; beat until thoroughly blended. Stir in flour gradually. Chill several hours. Beat egg whites slightly. Using one tablespoon of dough for each cookie, roll into balls. Brush lightly with egg white. Place on greased cookie sheet, leaving two-inch space between each cookie. Bake at 375° for five minutes. Remove from oven.
Roll 1/2 tsp. of the chilled pecan filling into a ball and firmly press into the center of each cookie.
Return to oven bake 5 minutes longer or until lightly browned. Cool 5 minutes on cookie sheets. Remove; cool completely on rack. Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Put chicken in greased baking dish and sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Top with sauerkraut and cheese.
Spoon dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle with parsley to serve.

title: grandma achilles' spiced tea(from the files of leota tarpy achilles)
directions: Bring to boil the water, cloves, cinnamon and tea.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put lid on and steep for 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags and cloves.
Add remaining ingredients.
Store in refrigerator. Leave cinnamon sticks in.
Add 4 teaspoons to each cup of hot water when serving.
A family favorite!

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Let congeal slightly.
Then mix soft cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and Jell-O mixture.
Beat well.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: rice and ground beef
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add puree with spices, onion and green pepper.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Mix with cooked rice.
Put in a baking dish and sprinkle with grated Romano. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and cut in thin slices.
Fill casserole dish about half full of apples.
Cover apples with water.
Sprinkle with apple pie spice.
Then melt the margarine.
Add to flour and sugar.
Mix and sprinkle over top of apples.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: summer corn chowder
directions: Melt the margarine in a large saucepan. Add onions and flour. Cook for 1 minute. Stir in water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve cubes.
Stir in corn, tomatoes and thyme. Heat to boiling. Cover and simmer soup over low heat for 20 minutes.
Stir in milk and salt.
Heat through.
Serves 6.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Stir condensed milk and whipped topping together in a large bowl until well blended.
Add pink lemonade and stir well.
Pour mixture into crust.
Chill and serve.

title: mrs. fields chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Before adding oatmeal, grind it in your blender, small amounts at a time.
Measure before grinding.
Mix in flour, oat flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add grated Hershey bar and chocolate chips.
Roll in golf ball sized balls on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion, pepper and tomatoes. Simmer 30 minutes.
Add spaghetti and cream of mushroom soup. Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Brown chicken; put on top of mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine crust ingredients and press into pie plate; bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, butter and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream. Gently spoon into crust.
Garnish with chocolate or cookie crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: polish sausage skillet dinner
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; place in skillet washed, sliced potatoes (leave skin on potatoes if desired, otherwise peel and slice).
Cook on medium heat about 8 minutes.
Slice onion and add onion slices to potatoes; stir and continue to simmer.
Cut Velveeta into bite sized cubes and add to top of potatoes and onions.
Turn heat to low.
Slice sausage into small slices.
Add to top of mix.
Cover and cook until potatoes are done.

title: watergate pudding
directions: Mix 2 boxes pistachio instant pudding as directed on box.
Add 1/2 bowl of Cool Whip.
Stir good.
Add pecan pieces, pineapple (drained) and miniature marshmallows.
Stir all this together and refrigerate for about an hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and sour cream.
Fold in berries.
Bake 350 degrees 1 hour in loaf pan.

title: v and o dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover and shake for 1 minute.
Chill for 20 minutes before serving.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: mardi gras casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth.
Add evaporated milk and cook until thick.
Add cheeses and stir until melted.
Place uncooked Minute rice or cooked rice in 7 x 11 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle oregano, cayenne pepper and parsley on rice.
Add water and stir to moisten. Layer tomatoes and onion, then tuna.
Pour cheese sauces over all.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour or can be made a day ahead.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies. I roll into small balls and press on cookie sheet.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Melt the butter in a top of the stove in casserole or a Dutch oven.
Add ham, onions and garlic.
Cook until lightly browned. Add green pepper, tomatoes, meat broth or chicken bouillon, bay leaf, thyme and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Gradually stir in rice. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until the rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Add shrimp and more seasoning, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, egg, cracker crumbs, onion, salt, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, oregano and pepper.
Shape into a 10 x 12-inch rectangle on waxed paper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up, jelly roll style, and press ends to seal.
Place in a shallow pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour the 2/3 cup tomato sauce over top and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and let set a few minutes before slicing.

title: neva's corn for freezer
directions: Mix together; bring to a boil and cook 20 minutes.
Stir frequently as it scorches easily.
Cool and freeze.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together in bowl first 4 ingredients.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and pour over first ingredients; mix.
Best made day before.
Sometime I add 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup raisins.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Place chicken over broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo and lemon juice. Pour over chicken.
(This sauce can be used over noodles and mixed vegetables and chicken, also.) Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: that good salad
directions: Combine oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper; shake well in a covered container.
Chill.
Toss romaine, tomatoes, Swiss cheese, almonds (if desired), parmesan cheese and bacon.
Shake dressing; pour over salad and toss.
Add croutons and serve immediately.
Yield:
14 servings.

title: mother's dumplings with chicken
directions: Cut flour, salt, pepper and shortening as one would for pie crust.
Then add beaten eggs and cut in.
Then add chicken broth a tablespoon at a time.
Form into ball.
Roll on floured pastry cloth, about 1/4-inch thick and cut into desired shapes.
Cook, debone and cut up chicken.
Drop dumplings into boiling broth from chicken; add 1/2 cup of milk and cook until tender.
Return chicken pieces to broth and dumplings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion and green pepper in oil. Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and stir until heated through.
Pour into a
greased casserole and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix with a fork in 2-quart bowl, sugar, flour, baking powder and shortening.
Stir in until well mixed milk and vanilla.
Stir in until coated with batter, nuts and apple. Spread in a greased 9-inch square pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit and gelatin in bowl until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in cottage cheese and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix everything together and place into a covered dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, tapioca, flour and salt; stir in rhubarb.
Spread mixture onto dough in 9-inch pie plate.
Dot with butter.
Top with remaining crust and crimp edges well. Brush top crust with beaten egg.
Cut vents in top dough.
Bake 55 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and Pet milk and cook, stirring at all times until it comes to a rolling boil; cook 5 minutes.
Take off heat; stir in 1 cup peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Pour in a buttered dish.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Mix well and simmer until cooked.
Put into scalded jars and seal.
May be put in hot water bath (boil) for 2 minutes or pressure cooker 5 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a 12-inch pizza pan.
Brown sausage and drain.
Sprinkle sausage over crust.
Sprinkle potatoes on crust.
Sprinkle cheese on crust (this can be done the night before).
Then mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave 3-in-1 dip
directions: Mix in 1-quart bowl all ingredients in microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Stir frequently. Serve hot or cold on chips or crackers.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in pan; season.
Melt butter in casserole dish; pour rice in dish.
Slice part of tomatoes, bell peppers and onions, making a layer of vegetables.
Add a layer of pork chops, then a layer of vegetables on top of chops.
Pour beef consomme and 1/2 can of water over this.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until chops are tender.

title: peach smash
directions: Place 4 pounds country-style ribs* in large pan; add enough water to cover.
Cover; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cook 1 hour.
Remove ribs; drain.
Place bone side down on grill 3-inches from medium coals.
Cook about 30 minutes, turning frequently.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Salt and pepper meat, then roll in flour.
In a large skillet, brown steak on both sides in a small amount of fat.
Pour tomatoes over steak, then add onion and green pepper.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour.
Occasionally, gently stir to keep steak from sticking to bottom of skillet. Serve over white or yellow rice.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream the sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Spread on plate.
Top with lettuce, tomato, onion and Cheddar cheese. Serve with nachos.

title: cream pralines
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and butter in a 2-quart saucepan; cook, stirring, over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add pecans; cook over medium heat to soft ball stage, 234°, stirring constantly.

title: chicken ham cheese spread
directions: Mix chicken, ham, cheese, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle parsley on top.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; set aside.
Cream butter. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add vanilla, beating well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Gradually add to cream mixture, beating well.
Stir in oats mixture.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured loaf pan (or 3 small pans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until bread tests done.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Saute garlic, onion and celery in butter until clear.
Remove garlic bulb and add parsley and oysters.
When oysters begin to curl, add bread crumbs and spices.
Stir in cream.
Butter turkey and then place stuffing inside.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Bring sugar and zucchini to a rolling boil.
Boil 10 minutes. Then add pineapple and boil for another 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add gelatin; stir until it is dissolved.
Place in jars and seal or freeze like freezer jelly.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix all ingredients except pecans. Form into ball and roll in 1 cup pecans.

title: buffalo style chicken wings
directions: Coat wings in flour, salt and pepper.
Heat Crisco in electric frypan.
Fry wings until crispy.
Dip fried wings into hot sauce mixture (margarine, garlic powder and celery salt).
Place dipped wings in pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with cut up celery and Marie's Bleu cheese mixed with 1 tablespoon celery seed.

title: butter roll
directions: Cream shortening into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk to consistency of biscuit dough.
Roll dough (1/2 recipe at a time); spread with butter.
Sprinkle each circle with 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon as desired.
Roll as for jelly roll and cut in 1-inch slices.
Place in greased pan and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruity dessert
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Combine fruit cocktail, pineapple, sweetened condensed milk and whipped topping, mixing until combined.
Pour into cookie lined pan; top with remaining cookies.
Refrigerate.

title: squash patties
directions: After cooking the squash, drain off the liquid.
Next, add flour, corn meal, egg, onion and pepper.
Let it all rise for 30 minutes.
Pat out and fry.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions together in 1/4 cup of water, adding salt and pepper.
Cook until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Grease baking dish with margarine.
Layer ingredients in dish starting with squash and onions, cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: clairmont diner cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in one egg at a time.
Add sugar, continuing to mix well until fully blended. Fold in vanilla and sour cream.
Bake at 350° to 375° for one hour and leave in oven with door slightly opened for an additional hour in well-greased 10-inch spring-form.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Put beef in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and saute onion; drain.
Add bacon, onion and remaining ingredients to beef.
Stir together well.
Cover and cook 4 to 6 hours.

title: spaghetti pie(microwave for 17 minutes.)
directions: On top of range, cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Stir butter or margarine into hot spaghetti. Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook on High, uncovered, for 2 minutes.
In 1 1/2-quart bowl, combine ground beef or sausage. Add onion and green pepper.
Cook, uncovered, at High for 5 minutes, stirring 3 times to break up meat.
Drain off excess fat. Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Cook, covered, at High until sauce is bubbly, 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring once.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Water and milk temperature should be 110° to 115°.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk and set aside.

title: old fashioned molasses cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and cream.
Add molasses, cinnamon and ginger.
Dissolve baking soda in a little boiling water.
Add to molasses mixture.
Be prepared to work fast (it will sizzle over); quickly add it to the first mixture.
Add flour, do not make the batter too thick.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stuffed chicken breast with gravy
directions: Stir hot water, 4 tablespoons of margarine and contents vegetable/seasoning packet in bowl until mixture is melted.
Add stuffing and egg until moistened.
Spoon stuffing onto chicken; wrap chicken around stuffing.
Place seam side down.
Grease shallow dish.
Brush with melted margarine.
Place remaining stuffing in center.
Heat gravy.
Pour over chicken.
Cover at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese 'n sausage strata
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add vegetables, continue cooking 5 minutes; drain.
Set aside to cool 10 minutes.
Stir together sausage mixture, Velveeta cheese and bread cubes; place in greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Beat milk and eggs.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Cover; refrigerate several hours.
Preheat oven to 350°. Remove cover.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish as desired.
Yields 6 servings.
(Prep time:
20 minutes plus chilling.
Cooking time:
1 hour.)

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Bring to boil the Coca-Cola, cocoa, cooking oil and margarine. Mix sugar, flour, eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Add boiled mixture and marshmallows.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 16.
Freezes well, but do not cook prior to freezing.

title: bob's quick yeast biscuit rolls
directions: Mix yeast in 3/4 cup warm water until dissolved.
Add milk. Add dry ingredients.
Knead on floured board and place in greased pans.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 15 minutes.
Uncooked dough will store in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Make package of stuffing mix. Slice thick pork chops 3/4 of the way open.
Stuff stuffing mix in pork chops. Place in oven-safe pan.
Put the rest of the stuffing mix around the pork chops.

title: forty minute chili
directions: In hot oil, brown onion and ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Combine and chill overnight.

title: duck gumbo
directions: *The gumbo file adds the characteristic "gumbo" flavor.

title: quiche
directions: Steam broccoli in steamer or microwave until crisp.
Place broccoli in lightly greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with onions, peppers and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients in blender and mix until smooth.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: punch
directions: This can be half frozen (not Sprite; keep it out until ready to serve).
Makes slush for hot weather.

title: freezer biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, sugar and baking powder together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Dissolve yeast in water and add to buttermilk.
Add buttermilk to flour all at once.
Stir dough until it follows fork around bowl.
Then put on floured surface and knead for 30 seconds.
Roll out 1-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Dough may be refrigerated for 4 to 5 days.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and place in greased baking dish.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Beat the butter at medium speed until creamy. Gradually add sugars, beating well. Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture, mixing after each addition. Divide dough into thirds and shape each portion into a ball (dough will be stiff). Cover and chill about 1 hour.

Remove 1 portion of dough from refrigerator at a time. Roll to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle on a lightly floured surface. Spread with 1/3 of the date filling, leaving a 1/2-inch margin on all sides. Starting at the long side, roll dough jelly roll fashion.
Pinch seams to seal.
Wrap in wax paper and freeze.
Repeat procedure with remaining dough.
Unwrap each roll and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick bottom of pie shell and bake for 8 minutes.
Toss cheese with flour and sprinkle in pie shell. Sprinkle ham on top of it.
Mix eggs, milk, onion, bell pepper and seasonings; pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 minutes or until set at 325°.

title: quick doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and beaten eggs together.
Mix all dry ingredients, then add milk.
Roll out and cut out doughnuts.
Deep fry in hot grease.

title: cookie pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake below oven center at 325° for 50 or 55 minutes.

title: raisin sauce
directions: In 1-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, heat to boiling 1/2 cup water, raisins, jelly, orange peel, salt and allspice.
In cup, stir cornstarch with orange juice until blended; stir into raisin mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear.
Serve hot on baked ham, baked or broiled poultry or roast pork.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Heat at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Dissolve gelatin in liquid.
Mix with mayonnaise. Add to finely chopped vegetables.
This is especially good in the spring or summer.

title: hot punch
directions: Mix and simmer until hot enough to drink.
The sticks will make it taste good.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff (set aside.).
Cook sugar, water, salt and corn syrup mixture until it spins a thread; quickly start beating egg whites again and pour in sugar mixture.
Beat for a few minutes.
Add flavor last.

title: pizza
directions: Dump on the sauce onto the dough and spread it with a big, flat spoon.
Sprinkle on the cheese.
Add all other ingredients. Bake pizza at 500° for 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and let cool for 4 minutes.
Cut it with a pizza cutter and put on a plate and eat it!

title: white fruit cake
directions: Prepare and chop nuts.
Cut up fruit and mix with enough flour to keep it from sticking together.
Cream butter, add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beat well after adding each egg. Add flour and orange juice alternately.
Add coconut, fruit and nuts.
Bake in large greased tubed pan at 250° to 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: spinach bread
directions: Cook spinach.
Saute onions and mushrooms in oleo.
Add drained spinach.
Remove from heat and add cheeses.
Slice bread into two halves.
Spread with mixture and wrap loosely in foil. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: crock-pot precooked ham
directions: Wrap precooked ham in foil and place in crock-pot.
Add potatoes that have been washed and wrapped in foil. Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or slow 6 to 7 hours.

title: christmas tree cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients.
When they are well mixed, shape with your hands into form of Christmas tree.
Cut olives crosswise; stick into tree all over.
Cover tree with chopped dry or fresh parsley; cut a star pattern of cardboard.
Cut slice of Cheddar about 1/4-inch thick.
Lay star pattern on cheese; carefully slice around pattern.
Insert toothpick (carefully) into base of star; set into tree top.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli; steam until tender.
Combine broccoli, onion and chicken broth in saucepan.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, simmer for 10 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir until smooth.
Stir in half and half.
Combine sauce and broccoli; cook over medium heat until soup bubbles.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Mix ground beef with soups.
Add corn and macaroni.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay Velveeta slices or cheese slices on top.
Place in oven at 350°.
Cook until cheese has melted and started to brown.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix together the bran flakes and boiling water. Let cool in buttermilk.
Mix together.
Add All-Bran, flour, baking soda and salt.
Bake in muffin tins at 375°.
Batter will keep in refrigerator.
Use as needed.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in Wesson oil.
Spread in deep casserole dish; add rice over pork chops, then tomatoes over rice.
Sprinkle with onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour water over entire mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Next day drain vegetables well.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Melt butter and add flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Add sour cream.
Cook slowly until thick.
Add green beans.
Put Swiss cheese on top.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lo-cal vegetable dip
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in blender until consistency of sour cream, then add rest of ingredients and blend until smooth.

title: ring tum diddy cheese dip
directions: Melt butter and add sharp cheese.
Stir continually until melted.
Add seasonings of salt, red pepper, dry mustard and Worcestershire.
